title: lime chicken
directions: Marinade:
Mix lemon juice, oil, honey, salt and pepper.

title: cheese straws
directions: Beat together margarine, cheese, egg and water.
Combine flour, salt, red pepper and paprika and add this dry mixture to the cheese mixture (add in 3 additions).
Set cookie press on thick, and put mixture through cookie press; or roll mixture and cut in circles. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: oven-fried kentucky chicken
directions: In a double plastic food bag, combine these coating ingredients well.
Shake mixture well.
Spray two 9 x 12 x 2-inch pans with Pam.
Run 16 pieces of chicken under cold water (two cut up fryers) in colander.
Drain off excess water.
Dredge pieces in flour mixture, one piece at a time and arrange skin side up on prepared pans.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine.
Apply in "dabs" with 1-inch wide pastry brush (drizzle does not work) until all margarine has been divided between chicken pieces.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and tender.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt broccoli, onion and oleo; let cool.
In medium bowl, beat eggs (lightly), then add cottage cheese and stir together.
Add broccoli mixture and cornbread mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Grate or cube cheese. Fry bacon crisp and crumble, then combine all together in large serving bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth. Stir in with other ingredients until all is well coated.
Chill for awhile before serving.
This keeps well in refrigerator in a tightly closed container.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into patties.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix pudding, brown sugar and nuts together.
Put dinner rolls in well buttered Bundt pan.
Pour melted margarine over rolls; sprinkle pudding mixture over rolls.
Cover with Saran Wrap and let sit out overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Put pork strips in crock-pot.
Add pepper and onion in bowl. Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice, vinegar, water and soy sauce.
Blend.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours.
One hour before serving, add pineapple.

title: crab frappe
directions: In a saucepan, heat the soup and add the dissolved gelatin. Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Put into a 4 c. mold and chill until set.
Invert onto a serving plate and serve with Ritz and/or other crackers.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, cabbage and green onion.
Combine noodles, sesame seed and almonds.
Melt 3 tablespoons of oleo and add noodle mixture and toast.
Mix with chicken and cabbage mixture.

title: very moist chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl blend together sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
In saucepan combine margarine, shortening and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir hot mixture into dry ingredients until smooth.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until done.
Pour Hot Fudge Frosting over warm cake in pan.

title: hawaiian punch pie
directions: Blend with a rubber scraper and pour into graham cracker crust. Keep in freezer until served.

title: "ghost" cake
directions: You will need a rectangular pan (13 x ?-inch).

title: tacos
directions: Cook ground beef with spices in skillet and drain.
Serve ground beef, tortillas, lettuce, tomato and onion and let everyone make their own.

title: old fashioned ginger molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat until blended.
Add molasses, vinegar and coffee.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 dozen.
They improve with age if stored in a tightly covered jar.

title: chocolate-dipped strawberries without tears
directions: Select large ripe unblemished strawberries, with stems if possible.
Wipe strawberries with a paper towel.
If you have to rinse them, dry well.
If strawberries are wet, chocolate will not adhere.
Place strawberries 2 inches apart on wax paper-lined cookie sheet and refrigerate.
If strawberries are cold when you dip them, chocolate will set quickly.
Chop chocolate into very small chunks and place in small deep bowl.
This allows dipping of strawberries up to hulls.
Melt chopped chocolate in microwave on high (100 percent power) for 1 minute.
Remove and stir until smooth.
White chocolate might need another 30 seconds.

title: mom's pecan crescent cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla for 5 minutes.
Gradually add flour and stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll walnut-sized pieces of dough into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
Form into crescent shapes and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes until cookies are lightly browned and firm to the touch.
While still warm, sprinkle on additional powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.
These cookies freeze well.

title: cabbage-red apple salad
directions: Combine cabbage, apple, celery and salt in a bowl.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten and toss.
Chill before serving.

title: leftover casserole
directions: Place ham, onion, garlic butter, garlic, salt and pepper in casserole.
Cover and microwave 3 minutes on High.
Mix in tomatoes, macaroni and green pepper.
Season generously.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat out rolls to cover baking sheet. Bake to directions on package. Mix cream cheese, salad dressing and dill dip. Spread onto cool crescent rolls. Place vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture. Place shredded cheese on top.

title: texas sauced dogs
directions: Saute franks and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and heat for 15 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Place oil in large frying pan.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper and cook until done.
Add ground chuck that has been salted and peppered.
Cook until done and browned.
Pour mixture into colander and drain.
Put mixture back in pan and add tomato sauce and catsup.
Simmer.
Place water in pot.
Add salt.
When water begins to boil, add spaghetti and cook until tender.
Drain.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.

title: bread and butter zucchini pickles
directions: Layer onions, zucchini and pepper with salt and ice cubes.
Let stand for 3 hours, adding more ice if needed.
Drain and divide into 2 batches.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over zucchini slices.
Heat to boiling.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: aunt verlia's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 300° and cook until a knife comes out clean when inserted into center.
Can be served with Cool Whip topping.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine the seasonings, mushroom soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine with other ingredients. Shape into patties.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomato if desired.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: This is a light and delicious dinner roll made from leftover Sourdough Pancake batter.
To at least 1 1/2 cups of leftover pancake batter, stir in enough flour, plus 1/2 teaspoon salt for each cup flour, to form stiff dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead, adding flour as necessary until it is smooth ball with satiny finish.
Place in a greased bowl, brush with melted butter and allow to rise in a warm place for about 1 hour.

title: rosemary baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a baking pan with aluminum foil. In a bowl, combine oil, garlic and 1 teaspoon rosemary.
Using another bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and 1 1/2 teaspoons rosemary.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan. Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Place potatoes around chicken. Drizzle oil mixture over chicken and potatoes.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°.
Bake until potatoes are tender, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour turkey loaf
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Let set until cracker crumbs are completely soft.
Combine the meat mixture with the next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into loaf.
Place into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.
Pour off excess liquid.
Slice and spoon sweet and sour sauce over top.
Serves 10 people.

title: 2 gallon ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar.
Beat until well mixed. Add cans of milk and vanilla flavoring.
Add fruit, if desired.
I use 5 ripe bananas or as much blended fruit as wanted.
You may need more sugar, if fruit is used.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: gratin dauphinois(creamed potatoes)
directions: Heat butter over moderate heat until melted.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Combine cabbage and mashed potatoes.
Add to skillet; press with fork to form large cake.
Cook over moderate heat until well browned.
Loosen potato cake with spatula; slide onto plate.
Flip back into skillet, uncooked side down.
Cook until well browned.
Serve this cut into wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli.
Mix broccoli, eggs, margarine, onions, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour	into casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crushed Ritz crackers and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs and stir in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (depending on size of dish).

title: ol' time bread pudding
directions: Into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, put toast, sprinkle with raisins.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla. Pour over toast and raisins.
Let stand 10 minutes then sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in moderately slow oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato soup
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine potatoes, water or broth, garlic, onion, bay leaf and salt in saucepan.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Cool slightly, then remove bay leaf.
Puree potatoes; place back into saucepan and gradually stir in milk.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste. Serve.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pat into a loaf pan.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil and cover with the catsup and return to oven for an additional 15 minutes.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually stir sugar; fold in nuts and chocolate bits.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 10 minutes.

title: gloria's lemon pie
directions: Beat together.
Pour in a crumb crust.
Garnish if desired. Chill.

title: tuna-noodle-casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water. Drain water or oil off tuna.
Add tuna and mushroom soup to noodles.
If desired, add peas.
Place in casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Pour over the top.
Crumble some plain potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Place in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy no-knead bread
directions: Combine first 4 dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Heat next 3 ingredients in a saucepan over low heat until warm.
Add egg and warm liquid to combined flour mixture.
Blend at lowest speed until moistened, then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

By hand, stir in another 2 1/2 cups flour to form a stiff batter. Cover dough; let rise in a warm place until light and doubled. Stir dough down; spoon into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 2-quart deep round casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Remove immediately; brush with butter.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place layers of asparagus and sliced eggs in a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Pour 1/2 can of soup over this.
Repeat layers of asparagus and sliced eggs.
Pour remainder of soup over this and cover with cheese again.
Cover and bake at 350°
until top bubbles.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and spread between 3 cookies. Freeze for 24 hours in covered pan.
Cover cookies with cool whip and roll in coconut.
Freeze again. These keep well in the freezer.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1 layer of cake into punch bowl.
Add 1/2 of vanilla instant pudding, half of crushed pineapple, half of pie filling and half of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: the charleston
directions: To make
corn
relish,	combine corn, raisins, vinegar, onion, bell pepper, sugar, mustard seed, dry mustard, salt and pepper flakes.
Bring
to	boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Place all (in order given) in large bowl.
Mash and squeeze (with hands) until thoroughly mixed.
Place small balls (with less than a teaspoon) on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of a glass; dip in sugar, then press balls flat.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and 1/4 cup water until it reaches 275°.
Add butter and peanuts.
Turn down heat, stirring while cooking, until it reaches 300°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart size casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Stir in carrots and slightly beaten egg. Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies will not brown very much.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Add ham pieces and all other ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange vegetables and chicken.
Combine soup and milk. Pour over broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: apple raisin pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt. Brown on both sides in oil in a large skillet.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; pour over chops.
Cut apples into 1/2-inch wedges. Place apples on pork chops.
Sprinkle raisins over all.
Cover and boil gently, about 25 minutes.
Remove chops with apples and raisins to heated platter.
Combine flour and small amount of Vitamite milk to make a paste.
Gradually stir in remaining milk and salt.
Add to skillet, stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Serve over pork chops.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Spice Cookies:
Add 1 teaspoon each:
cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
For Chocolate Cookies:
Add 3 tablespoons cocoa with flour.
Other Combinations:
Add 1 cup chopped nuts or 1 cup raisins or 1 cup dates or 1 cup oats (or any combination you desire).

title: fifteen bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Let soak in two quarts of water overnight or a minimum of 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Cook in 2 quarts of water and tablespoon salt for approximately 2 hours.
Add onion, black pepper, tomatoes and summer sausage.
Then cook another 45 minutes.
Add chickpeas, black-eyed peas and package of Cajun seasoning (season to taste).
Cook 15 more minutes, then serve.
Serves approximately 10 persons.
Excellent with white or brown rice on the side and cornbread.

title: gourmet buffet potatoes
directions: Melt butter and cream cheese in pan carefully; stir continuously.
Add soup and onion and heat, stirring until smooth. In a large casserole, layer half the potatoes and half the sauce; repeat.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: philly sub
directions: Slice roll down center.
Sprinkle lightly with olive oil. Arrange spiced ham on roll followed by the cooked salami, hard salami and Provolone cheese.
Arrange onion, tomato and pickle slices.
Top with salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Add shredded lettuce and slice of boiled ham.

title: pineapple cooler
directions: Combine juice and ice cream.
Beat with a rotary beater until frothy.
Serve immediately with straw or spoon.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. May add mashed bananas or strawberries.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil gizzards and livers until tender.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in 4 tablespoons oil until light brown, then mix sauteed ingredients.
Cook rice in small amount water for 30 minutes.
Pour rice into the other ingredients.
Add Worcestershire sauce and place over heat for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: fresh pea soup
directions: Shell peas and measure about 2 cups; set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt the butter.
Add the onion and saute until tender. In a separate saucepan add 1/2 cup chicken stock to the fresh peas. Cover and steam about 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add the peas and remaining chicken stock to the sauteed onions; cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Puree about 1/3 of the mixture at a time in a blender or food processor.
Return puree to the saucepan and stir in the cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
You may also add snipped fresh herbs such as dill, parsley, chives or basil.
Serves 4.

title: arizona salad
directions: Blend ingredients together; keep in refrigerator overnight. This gives sour cream time to sweeten.
Serve on lettuce leaves for salad or plain for dessert.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in 2 quarts cold water.
Pour over the sliced cucumbers and onions.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Drain well.

title: enchiladas casserole
directions: Fry ground beef.
Drain grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup, can of mushrooms, onions, green chiles and bell pepper.
Mix in a large mixing bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fry tortilla shells until they are a crispy golden brown.
When the shells are cool, crumble 4 shells in the bottom of an oblong baking dish. Pour mixture on top.
Crumble remaining shells on top of mixture and spread shredded cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted on top, approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.
Also good served with sour cream.

title: herbed vinegar
directions: Note:
Apple cider vinegar may be used.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add water and Ragu.
Simmer 10 minutes. Cook 9 slices lasagna noodles; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl and mix well.	Put 1 cup sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 pan, 3 slices lasagna and cheese mixture. Alternate, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date pie
directions: In a double boiler cook dates and milk until thick.
Add sugar, flour, salt and yolks.
Cook all together until thick.
Place in baked pie crust.
Can use whites of eggs for a meringue or put whipped cream on top.

title: sugarless raspberry nut bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour and pecans. Press half of dough in greased glass baking dish. Spread jam over dough. Dust remaining dough with flour and roll dough to fit top. Place over jam to completely cover. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza spread
directions: In a saucepan, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Stir in marinara sauce and oregano. Gradually stir in cheese until melted. Pour into a fondue pot or small slow cooker to keep warm. Serve with bread.

title: chocolate delightful
directions: Bake cake using light recipe:
2 eggs, 1 1/2 cups water, no oil.
Whip pudding according to box instructions and place in refrigerator for a little while.
Freeze candy bars, then crush using end of cleaver.
When cake cools, crumble.
In a large glass bowl, make layers of cake, pudding, Cool Whip and sprinkle candy. Repeat 2 to 3 layers.
Refrigerate overnight or put in freezer until time to serve.

title: brownies
directions: Cream oil and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat.
Then add cocoa mixed in hot water.
Stir in flour.
Mix and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Can also add nuts.

title: skillet supper
directions: Spread cabbage over melted margarine in deep skillet; top with hamburger, rice and onion.
Pour tomato sauce over; cover and cook on low heat, 35 to 40 minutes without lifting lid.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine ingredients and chill about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings. Decorate top with red and green maraschino cherries and pecan halves, if desired.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix flour with cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell or quiche pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let set for a few minutes before cutting.

title: chicken cornelias(serves: 14 portions)
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika chicken and lay, not touching, in large pan.
Mix together soups, whipping cream and vermouth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour at 350°. Just before serving, add sauteed mushrooms and celery.
Serves well with rice, carrots and a green vegetable.

title: 7 layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Cover well with mayonnaise. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Sprinkle bacon bits over cheese. Refrigerate.

title: old mexico chili
directions: 1926 Method:
Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 cup water. Stir, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally; or place all in crock-pot.
Mix well and cover.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 5 hours).

title: parmesan fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Place fish fillets in shallow "buttered" pan (use margarine if you prefer) and season with salt and pepper. Spread tomato sauce over fillets and sprinkle with cheese. Drizzle melted margarine over fillets.
Bake, uncovered, until fish flakes easily, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: white icing
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Cook until syrup strings like a hair on a fork.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup slowly, while beating with mixer into egg whites.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.

title: garlic tomatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Good over lettuce, with other vegetables or alone.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine sugar with liquid ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, then add blueberries.
Grease muffin tin or spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: potato curry
directions: Saute onion lightly in oil and then add curry to blend.
Add potatoes and salt.
Fry until potatoes are done.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Place ham slice first, then cheese, then turkey breast. Place 1/2
cup
stuffing	mix on the turkey breast.
Roll up. Place seam side down in a large casserole dish.
You may cover with
a chicken gravy or cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: corn sausage casserole
directions: Mix together. Pour into greased round 8-inch casserole. Spread catsup on top.
Bake in pan of water 1 inch deep at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls. bake in 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
(I prefer hot sausage and extra sharp cheddar with a dash or 2 of tabasco sauce.)

title: mexican tacos
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer 10 - 15 minutes. Serve on tortillas with cheese, chopped lettuce and tomatoes.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat for 2 minutes. Add frozen spinach; cover pan and reduce heat until spinach has thawed (do not overcook).
Add cooked rice, cheese, milk, soy sauce and salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Save directly from pan or turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese has melted (350°).
Can be frozen and reheated later.

title: chocolate chip banana muffins
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift flour with salt and baking powder; add to brown sugar mixture, stirring until blended.
Add bananas and beat until mixture is smooth.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spoon batter into greased (or paper lined) muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pina colada(non-alcoholic)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until frothy, about 1 minute. Serves 3.

title: garlic toast
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan. Add garlic powder and mix well. Brush on or dip sliced bread (slice 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick). Make sure both sides are covered. Place on baking sheet under broiler until brown. Turn; sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Return to broiler until golden. Serve. Can reheat in oven.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Heat applesauce in saucepan until bubbling starts.
Dissolve jello in hot applesauce.
Remove from heat.
Add 7-Up.
Mix.
Pour into mold and cool.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place ingredients in a casserole in order given; salt and pepper chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (covering dish). Remove cover and bake or broil 5 minutes until brown.

title: corn casserole #3
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour or until browned.

title: mince meat cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into first mixture.
Add mince meat broken into fine pieces with fork.
Pour into prepared loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve with hard sauce.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Beat butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Fold in half the flour, then half the milk.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Scoop batter into liners in tins.
Sprinkle generously with nutmeg sugar.
Bake for 20 or 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini "apple pie"
directions: Peel and cut zucchini lengthwise.
Remove seeds and cut in slices.
Cook until barely tender.
Drain and place in ice cold water 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: fourfold delight
directions: Melt oleo; add pecans and flour.
Press into 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. Cool crust.

title: falafel
directions: Process garbanzo beans, onion, garlic, bread, cumin and chilies in a blender or food processor until smooth, then spoon mixture into a bowl.
Add parsley, salt, pepper and egg; mix well. form in 8 balls and coat in bread crumbs.
Flatten balls slightly to form oval shapes.
Half fill a deep-fat fryer or saucepan with oil; heat to 375°F (190°C) or until a 1/2-inch cube of day-old bread browns in 40 seconds.
Fry Falafel, a few at a time, 3 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Cut pita bread in half and open to form pockets.
Put 1 Falafel into each pocket with lettuce, onion and tomato slices and serve hot. Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: *Or use 1 (20 ounce) package of frozen combination.

title: spicy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a baking pan or dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Saute garlic in oil, then brown chicken in the oil.
Place chicken in deep casserole.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water and add to oil in which chicken was browned along with mushrooms and artichokes.

title: mexican meat loaf(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9-inch skillet, heat oil over medium heat; add onions, peppers, garlic and broth mix.
Saute until onions are translucent.
In medium bowl, combine sauteed vegetables with remaining ingredients.
Shape mixture into a loaf and place in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake until browned, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
(On Weight Watchers Program, each serving provides 4 P, 1 B, 1 1/2 V, 1 FA, 15 opt. calories.)

title: black forest cherry torte(schwarzwalder kirschtorte)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together 3 times.
Beat eggs until light and thickened (about 10 minutes).
Gradually add sugar to eggs, beating constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Fold in flour, a little at a time. Add the hot milk, mixing quickly until batter is smooth.
Lightly grease with flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans, preferably pans with removable bottoms.
Divide the batter between the 3 pans.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake cake layers for 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven and invert pans until cake is cool.
Remove from pans and slice each layer crosswise into 2 layers, making 6 layers.

title: macaroni and bean soup
directions: In a large pot, heat olive oil and cook carrots, celery and onion until tender. Add tomatoes with their liquid, broth, water, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Drain white and red kidney beans.
In a small bowl, with fork, mash one can white beans. Add to pot and stir in well.
Add remaining 2 cans drained beans, cooked pasta and frozen spinach which has been defrosted and drained.
Heat through and serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: banana pudding(one of bro. s. c. perkins' favorite desserts)
directions: Combine pudding and milk according to instructions on box. Then add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Assemble alternate layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix until all ingredients are used.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil coffee in 1 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer 45 minutes; very slowly.
Strain twice, should be about 1 1/2 cups of coffee extract.
Boil sugar in 1 quart of water for 5 minutes, let cool. Add cool coffee extract to cool sugar syrup, then add in 1 quart of alcohol, stir.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Should make about 3 quarts of Kahlua.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and run on high speed for a few seconds, until smooth in texture.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients very well.
Cook for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Serve hot or warm.

title: audrey's zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 bread pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes two loaves.
(You can add nuts or raisins if desired, about 1 cup.)
To serve, spread with cream cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add flour and sour cream alternately. Mix well.
Add oil and vanilla; mix until batter is well blended (3 minutes on medium speed).
Pour into tube pan.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and onions together.
Spread on bottom of 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch glass shallow bowl or pan.
Spread cocktail sauce over this mixture. Sprinkle crab meat over cocktail sauce.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: puppy chow(cereal snack)
directions: Mix in a large bowl the first 3 ingredients.
Melt in saucepan the margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour melted mixture over dry mixture and coat the cereal with chocolate mixture. Sprinkle with the powdered sugar.
Put lid on and shake to coat all of the cereal with the sugar.

title: ground beef dressing
directions: Cook beef just until redness is gone.
Drain all fat.
Combine bread crumbs and poultry seasoning and add to meat.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in covered casserole dish 45 to 50 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken with onions, bell pepper and celery.
Crumble cornbread; add chicken broth, more celery, onions and bell pepper. Fry sausage and crumble on top.
Bake at 325°.

title: potato salad for fifty
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Dice while warm.
Make marinade of oil, vinegar, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add warm potatoes and mix gently.
Marinate until cool.
Add eggs, celery, onion and pepper to marinated potatoes.
Mix lightly.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix carefully to blend.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
With 1/2 cup portions it will serve 50.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onions, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread Miracle Whip over entire salad.
Sprinkle sugar over Miracle Whip.
Seal all the salad with the Miracle Whip. Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Mix and serve in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with hands.
Form into walnut-size balls and chill.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip balls in the chocolate and put on waxed paper.
Makes about 50 balls.

title: mexican squash
directions: Combine in a saucepan the squash, salt, sugar, pepper and onion; simmer in a small amount of water until tender.
Remove from heat and drain well by mashing in a colander.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Add milk and cheese.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low-fat meat 'n gravy
directions: Coat a heavy pan with no stick Pam spray.
Brown meat and onion, stirring often; if desired, drain fat.
Add salt, pepper and flour; stir until flour is absorbed.
Add milk and water. Cook until liquid thickens.
If a thinner gravy is desired, add more milk or water.

title: shaker pumpkin loaves
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices together.
Set aside; mix sugar and margarine until blended; add eggs and beat in pumpkin, then add flour.
Pour into greased pans and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at about 325°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with Hawaiian or pumpernickel bread.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute' vegetables in butter until tender.
Add flour to vegetables and stir until smooth.
Dissolve base in water; blend into vegetables.

title: oven-sliced potatoes
directions: In large shallow greased baking dish, arrange potato slices in layers.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Brush potato slices with butter mixture.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are crisp and brown.
Serves 4.

title: chicken a la king(from overrock inn)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter.
Add soup diluted with 1/2 can of water and cut-up cooked chicken.
Add parsley, pimento and cooked peas.
Serve on biscuits, toast points or patty shells.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add nutmeats and combine with the first mixture. Form dough in long roll and place in icebox overnight.
In the morning, slice thin and bake on a lightly greased baking sheet at 375°; about 5 minutes will be enough, but watch cookies carefully.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, using a whisk, beat the egg and egg whites until foamy. Add the next 4 ingredients; beat well and set aside. Preheat oven to 200°. Lightly coat the skillet with butter over medium heat. Dip bread slices into the egg mixture, turning to coat and draining the excess back into dish. Place bread slices in prepared skillet. Cook until golden brown, turning once, about 1 to 2 minutes per side. Transfer cooked slices to a plate; keep warm in oven. Add butter as needed to skillet.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer the first 3 ingredients for 2 hours with cover slightly tipped.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add the vodka and vanilla.

title: tomato and corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Nice served in lettuce cups with dollop of mayo on top.
Serves 4.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in hot milk and pour over crumbs.
Beat eggs.
Add to squash, crumbs, milk and onion mixture.
Bake in greased casserole dish in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ye olde south wassail
directions: Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove spices.

title: bean soup
directions: Put potatoes in large pot with enough water to cover.
Cook until almost done.
In meantime, cut up all other ingredients. Add rest and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Don't drain potatoes; may need to add water.
This is great for crock-pot.
Just put all ingredients in crock-pot with water to cover well.
Cook on low all day.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine oil, water, eggs and pumpkin. Stir until well mixed.
Mix dates, raisins and nuts in 1/2 cup flour, coating well. In a large bowl, combine flour and all other ingredients. Add liquid and stir just until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and dates. Put into pans.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix together and put in a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rouladen
directions: Lightly pound steaks.
Streak mustard on steak, adding salt and pepper.
Dice onion and bacon and mix together.
Add equal amounts to each steak, spreading evenly.
Start with the smaller end, roll the steak forward and fasten with a clamp or a string. Brown evenly using butter or margarine.
Add 2 cups (1/2 liter) water; cover and bake in moderate oven (325° to 350°) for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken with flour and water to which a little salt is added.

title: chilled shoe peg corn
directions: Drain corn and put in bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix. Store in refrigerator.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 pan. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
I double this for a large crowd.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix in bowl.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: family's favorite banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs.
Mix the bananas with the lemon juice and mix into the batter.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: In large pan, saute cabbage and onion in margarine 10 minutes or until brown.
Add water, cover and cook over high heat 2 minutes until water evaporates.
Add noodles, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 8 servings.
Good hot or cold.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add cut apples. Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and add to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix all together.
Dough will be very stiff.
Bake in 9x13 pan at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Crunch:
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, mix flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted butter. Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes. Stir often; set aside.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta "al dente" according to package directions.
As pasta cooks, heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add flour. Cook, stirring, a few minutes.
Add pepper and salt.
Slowly stir in broth.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until slightly thickened. Stir in half and half, chicken and 3/4 cup cheese.

title: kansas city apple cake
directions: Combine the flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for about an hour or until done.
This is better if it is made a day ahead.

title: killer brownies
directions: Make brownie mix according to package directions.
I usually use the kind that has chocolate packet to be added.
Mix in sour cream and chocolate chips.
Bake just under recommended time for gooey brownies.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Place yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, put warm liquid molasses, salt and oil, then add yeast and stir.
Sift in about half or 2/3 of flour and stir.
Continue adding flour until the dough is stiff enough to work by hand on floured counter top.
Knead until smooth, cover and let set about 15 minutes.
Knead again, place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Knead and shape into loaves.
Place in loaf pans, cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour depending on size of loaves.
Less time for smaller loaves.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Chop or break all vegetables and put in a large bowl.
Add chicken pieces.
Toss.
Add almonds, rice, noodles and dressing just before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Flour meat, then brown in shortening; drain fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir.
Add green pepper; continue to cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put flour in big bowl and make hole in center.
In separate bowl, mix yeast, warm water, oil and sugar.
Add to hole in flour. Stir until smooth.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Roll into balls to make biscuits.
Place in greased baking pan and allow to rise.
Place in oven and bake at 350° or until golden brown.
Can be used for kolache and cinnamon rolls.

title: raspberry cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients with a mixer.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: diane's lasagna concoction
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Boil noodles until tender.
Rinse and drain.
Layer 1/2 of noodles in bottom of 9 x 13 pan, followed by 1/2 of cottage cheese and egg mixture, 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 of meat mixture and 1/2 of Parmesan cheese.
Add remaining ingredients in same order.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar and butter, beat into mixture the eggs and bananas (mash bananas before adding).
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into loaf pans and bake one hour.
Test in 45 minutes with toothpick.
Bake at 300°.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn to continue cooling.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and soda.
Boil together margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; mix.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan; cool.

title: spittini
directions: May be served as an entree or appetizer.
In a large skillet, brown chopped onions in oil.
Mix browned onions in a large mixing bowl with breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
Divide filling into 10 to 12 servings and spread mixture onto a 1 1/2 pound of pounded round steak or veal, cut into 10 to 12 servings (1 1/2 x 2-inches).
Then spread mixture onto your 10 to 12 pieces of meat.
Roll each piece with mixture inside and fasten with a wooden toothpick that has been dipped in oil. Place in baking dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: egg roll
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients to meat loaf consistency.
Roll up into egg roll wrappers and deep fry in oil until golden brown.

title: pumpkin dump bread
directions: Note:
If you use pie mix, omit the spices.
If you use regular pumpkin, add spices.

title: barbecued pork shoulder
directions: Cover roast with lightly salted water in a large Dutch oven. Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender. Drain and slice thinly; place in a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Combine next 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon sauce over sliced roast, turning slices to coat.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serve on buns, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. In large bowl with fork, mix flour with next 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients (except nuts) and mix just until blended. Add nuts; turn batter into pans.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on rack.
When cool, wrap each loaf and store at room temperature (can be frozen).

title: my mother's famous cream corn(south georgia style)
directions: Hush and de-silk the corn as soon as possible after picking. Rinse the ears and pat dry.
Working from stalk end to tassel end, barely snip the tops off the kernels.
You need a very sharp knife for this.
You must not cut deep into the kernel or the corn will not be creamy.
After cutting each ear in this manner, scrape the "cream" from each kernel by pulling a dull knife over it.
This releases all the remaining starch for "creaming."
Then pour the corn mixture and starchy water into a heavy baking dish such as Corning Ware.
Add enough water to make a soupy mixture.
Then add salt and fat and cook in the microwave.

(Mother cooked on top of the stove in a large frypan, cooking and stirring until it thickened to the desired consistency, but this required much watching and stirring to prevent it from sticking, so I prefer the microwave.)
Cover and bring to boil on High setting.
Stir and continue cooking (on Low setting) and stirring at about 3 to 5 minute intervals.
If it thickens too much, add a little more water.
If it doesn't thicken enough, remove the lid and cook at a little higher setting to let some of the water evaporate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs well; add all ingredients except grated cheese. Layer bean mixture with cheese in a baking dish, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pot roast with vegetables
directions: Season pot roast with salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Make slits in roast with a sharp knife.
Put a little more salt, pepper and oregano, along with the garlic and parsley, in each slit. Coat the roast with flour.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Mix together the sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Boil for 10 minutes; cool.
Add to mixture the frozen juices.
Add 1/2 can of water to each can of juice.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 1 quart of water and 2 cups of sugar.
Mix together with juices and other 3 quarts of water.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve, one bottle or two.

title: coke a chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and salt.
In saucepan, mix catsup, steak sauce, onion salt and garlic salt.
When mixture is hot, add celery salt and red pepper.
Turn chicken pieces in hot mixture. Add Coke.
Cover and let cook until tender on low heat.
Remove lid and cook until liquid cooks down.

title: vegetable fettuccine
directions: In 11 x 7-inch baking dish, dissolve broth; mix in 1/4 cup water.
Add carrots; microwave covered (wax paper) on High 3 to 4 minutes until softened.
Add bell pepper and zucchini or squash; microwave covered on High 3 to 4 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring halfway through cooking.
Stir in fettuccini and margarine; toss gently to combine.
Sprinkle with scallions and black pepper.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix together cabbage, onions and almonds.
In a jar mix vinegar, oil, sugar and flavoring packet from the noodle soup. When ready to serve, pour dressing over cabbage mixture.
Crunch up the Top Ramen noodles right when ready to serve.

title: mom's raisin cream pie
directions: Boil raisins in a little water.
Set aside.
Combine brown sugar, egg yolks and cornstarch.
Make a paste of cornstarch by adding a little milk.
Boil to thicken.
Add raisins.
Put in a baked crust and top with meringue.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add salt. Stir in flour, mixing well to blend. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and nuts. Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes in 350° oven; layers, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients in the order listed.
Beat well. Drop cookies by spoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pecans
directions: Mix in a saucepan and heat until butter is melted.
Bake pecans for 15 minutes.
Turn over and pour cooked sauce on
and bake another 15 minutes.
Turn once.
Put on baking sheet.
Put on paper towel and drain grease off.
Place in serving basket after cool, lined with paper napkin.
(Oven temperature 300°.)

title: beef-rice casserole
directions: Brown beef in hot fat.
Add rice, soup, water, salt, celery and green peppers.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole; cover and bake
1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: glazed carrots and apples
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole. Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High about 8 minutes or until carrots are crisp-tender, stirring once during cooking.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spinach frittata
directions: Put a little oil in a flat pan and wait until it's hot.
Mix the eggs and pour them in the flat pan.
Add the cooked spinach and mix with the egg.
Then add shredded Mozzarella (and Ricotta). Wait until the bottom is all dried up.
Put a flat dish over the pan and turn it over so the frittata is on the dish and slide it back in the pan.
Cook the other side, your omelet (frittata) should be light brown on the edges.

title: boiled frosting
directions: Heat sugar, cream of tartar, salt and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil without stirring to 260° on candy thermometer (hard boil stage).
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Pour syrup in thin stream into whites, beating constantly. Add vanilla.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: Dissolve jello in the 2 cups of hot water.
Add lemon juice. When it's cooler, add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole.
Chill overnight.

title: dill sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
Makes 1 cup.
Good over fish.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place sliced zucchini, chopped onion, salt, pepper and grated cheese and parsley in oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle Bisquick on top.
Beat eggs with oil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cover with foil.

title: breakfast breads
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain well. Break bacon in 1/2-inch pieces.
Beat together butter and sugar until fluffy; beat in egg.
Combine flour and baking soda; stir into butter mixture.
Stir in bacon, corn flakes and raisins. Drop by rounded tablespoons, 2-inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to racks to cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cucumber salad(low calorie)
directions: Skin cucumber and cut into slices. Add to mixing bowl, sliced cucumber, raisins, chives, mint flakes and yogurt.

Mix together. Add more yogurt, if desired, but a little bit goes a long way. Let flavors blend in refrigerator for 15 to 30 minutes (but no longer than 30 minutes). Serve within 30 minutes of adding yogurt to cucumber.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar with a
mixer to make a fluff. Add eggs, then add salt and pepper. Then add half and half. Put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, broccoli and egg in casserole dish.
Top with crumbs and butter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add cans of soup to beef.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Top with Tater Tots. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until done; drain.
In a large bowl, mix soups, milk and enchilada sauce, then add meat and onion mixture. Place chips in greased casserole dish.
Cover with meat mixture and Velveeta cheese.
Alternate layers and bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine; combine other ingredients, reserving half of stuffing for topping.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pizza casserole
directions: *Use any preference of cheese.

title: wesson flaky pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in Wesson or Crisco, using your hands or pastry blender, until all flour is blended in, forming pea size chunks.
Sprinkle with water, one tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork until dough will form a ball. Divide dough into two parts.
Press between hands to form two 5 to 6-inch "pancakes."

title: garlic mashed red potatoes(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cook potatoes until done. Drain water. Add butter, milk, salt, and pepper. Mash ingredients. Stir in cheese.

title: pork chop and rice bake
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Pour rice over them.
Mix onion soup with bouillon and pour over rice and pork chops.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and set aside.
While cooking, mix soup and all ingredients, except Ritz crackers and cheese.
Mix broccoli with the other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Mix Ritz crackers and butter.
Top casserole with crackers and butter mix, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cranberries, pineapple and sugar together and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning, add the marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip.
Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, peel and dice potatoes.
Boil in lightly salted water until just done, but not mushy.
Drain potatoes and place in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
In medium saucepan, melt 6 tablespoons butter and blend in flour.
Gradually add cream, stirring.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Pour over potatoes and top with grated cheese.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter, stir in bread crumbs, mixing until coated.
Sprinkle over top of potatoes.
Bake for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Put half of dressing mix in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour on top of dressing mix.
Sprinkle balance of dressing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesettes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll between hands into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes a bunch!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add milk and sugar.
Mix cocoa with flour.
Add gradually, then butter and flavoring.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with beaten egg whites or Cool Whip.
If egg whites are used, place in heated oven to brown.
This makes 1 large pie.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour or until done. Test with pick.
Serve warm, especially good with cream cheese. You may skip the salt and butter flavoring, but increase the poppy seed to 2 tablespoons.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans slightly and add soup.
Mix together.
Add onions. Salt and pepper to taste and stir together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Over low heat, melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Mix together cooked broccoli, cooked onion, soup, rice and cheese. Bake in greased casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix oil and dry ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Blend well (place in large covered dish or bag and shake until blended). Spread on cookie sheet to dry.
Enjoy.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9 pan. Let cool. Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle. Mix topping and milk in bowl and cover cake. Pour 1/2 of crushed candy bars over cake. Top with Cool Whip, then with the rest of the candy bar.

title: lemon delights
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Put cookies on cookie sheet and barely pat tops. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Allow to cool.
This is also good with chocolate cake mix.
Substitute cocoa and sugar mixture for powdered sugar.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Add taco seasoning to water when you cook the chicken. Dice chicken and save 3 breasts for taco salad. Cool and refrigerate broth. Remove fat from top. To broth, add tomatoes, corn and green onions. When soup comes to a boil, add rice, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients, sift together the dry ingredients, set aside.
Add to first ingredients the apples, nuts and vanilla. Blend this mixture with the dry ingredients.
Mix well, pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 45-60 min. or until toothpick comes out clean.
This is also good in a 9 by 13 in. flat cake pan. Frost with caramel frosting.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Flake tuna. Add carrots, celery, onion and mayonnaise. Chill. Fold in noodles just before serving. Place salad on large lettuce leaf. Serve with a roll and fruit.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop vegetables finely.
Saute all vegetables in 1 stick (1/2 cup) margarine until tender.
Add chicken broth and bring to boil. Reduce heat and cook for 30 minutes.
Add potato soup and cook for 10 minutes.
Add Velveeta chopped in small squares.
Allow to melt.
Add sour cream and stir until mixed well.
Serve hot.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour; blend in shortening until crumbs are the size of peas.
Beat egg; add vinegar, salt and water.
Mix with fork until mixture leaves sides of bowl and forms a ball.
Makes pastry for two 2 crust pies.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Chill in cold water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Serves about 10 people or 4 if my son is home.

title: aunt lela's overnight cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onion in bowl, starting with and ending with cabbage.
Cover with sugar.
Do not mix together.
In a saucepan boil together vinegar, oil, 2 teaspoons sugar, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Do not mix.
Cover and chill overnight.
Next day stir or toss so it is mixed. Serve.
This will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: turnips with caraway seed
directions: Cook turnips until quite tender; mash and season with butter, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Beat together thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dill bread
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed,
salt,
soda
and
dry
yeast.
In
saucepan,
heat cottage cheese,
water
and butter until mixture is warm.
Add egg and warm
liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at lowest speed until moistened;
beat
minutes
at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining
flour
to
form a stiff dough.
Cover; let rise in warm
place
until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour.
Stir down batter.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round (1 1/2
to 2-quart) casserole.
Cover, let rise in warm place until light, 30
to
minutes.
Bake
at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.
Brush with butter.

title: big and easy biscuit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Separate biscuits in 2 layers.
Arrange in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll or 12-inch pizza pan.
Press biscuits to form crust.
Spread tomato sauce over dough; sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Stir salad dressing mix into prepared ground beef; spoon over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine melted margarine, 1 egg and the cake mix in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Press over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan to make a crust.

title: italian pork steak
directions: Arrange pork in microwave-proof dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches, with meaty edges to outside.
Place sausage on pork.
Cover tightly and microwave on Medium (50%) for 15 minutes. rotating dish 1/4 turn every 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: banana muffins for diabetics
directions: Beat egg, Sweet 'N Low and oil. Add flour and bananas; mixture will be thick. Drop in paper lined muffin tins. Cook at 400° until golden brown.

title: eiere-koek(egg cake)
directions: Whip the egg whites until peaks form.
To the egg yolks, add sugar, flour, salt and water.
Mix well.
Fold into whites.
In heavy skillet, melt the margarine.
Turn to medium heat or slightly lower.
Add egg mixture.
Cover.
Check in 3 minutes.
When sides are browned and pull away from pan, it's ready.
Center will be softer.

title: quakers
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add in oats, then dry ingredients into batter. Beat well.
Put 1/4 cup sugar in a bowl, then pinch off dough and roll it into walnut size balls and roll in sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and stir with broccoli mixture. Refrigerate thoroughly before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine vinegar and honey and pour over cucumbers and green peppers.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together well.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Serve with warm chocolate sauce, if desired.

title: opera fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In medium saucepan, melt butter in milk.
Blend in frosting mix (dry).
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth and glossy. Remove from heat; stir in nuts.
Spread mixture evenly into buttered pan; cool until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 32 candies.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler on stove top.
Add nuts and noodles while morsels are still hot.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Allow morsels time to set.
Refrigerate after morsels have set.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cover bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan with chicken and chestnuts. Mix soup, cream or milk, mayonnaise and cheese in pan.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken.
Place cooked broccoli over chicken.
Cover with buttered croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 8-inch square dish with Pam, etc. Bake bread in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove.
Cool.
Break into pieces (small).

title: toasted coconut cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine Eagle Brand milk, egg yolks, water and pudding mix.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with remaining 1/4 cup coconut.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: eclair cake
directions: First, spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick spray. Put layer of graham crackers. Next, mix pudding and milk. When starts to thicken, fold in Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 of mixture onto the crackers, then add another layer of crackers. Put rest of mixture onto crackers. Top with remaining crackers. Frost crackers with icing. Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add flour and 7-Up; mix well. Beat eggs slightly, add to mixture.
Add flavors and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan (large).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake according to package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake.
Poke holes in top of warm cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk into holes.
Pour ice cream topping into same holes.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candy bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: billy bobs balls in beer
directions: Combine meat mixture, roll into balls, and brown in skillet. Pour off gravy.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Blend together the carrots, celery, pineapple and the pecans. Mix together with a small amount of mayonnaise and serve.
Serves about 8 to 10 people.

title: butter baked rice(serves 6 to 7)
directions: Combine salt and water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice. Let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse rice with cold water.
Drain well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until butter is almost absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour broth over.
Bake at 325°,
covered, for 45 minutes.
Add parsley; fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with almonds. Bake, uncovered, 10 minutes more.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute the onion and pepper in butter in a heavy soup pot.
Add the potatoes and enough water to just cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until the potatoes are done.
Mash some of the potatoes against the side of the pot or use a potato masher to mash some of them. Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with crusty bread, some mild cheese and a crisp salad.

title: baked brisket
directions: Sprinkle meat with seasoning; add chopped onion and bottle of liquid smoke.
Cover meat with foil and place in fridge overnight. Next day, place in 300° to 325° oven; be sure not
to uncover meat from foil after taking out of fridge.
Cook about 4 to 6 hours. After about the 4th hour of cooking, remove from oven, take off foil and pour barbecue sauce over meat, then continue cooking.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Remove brownies from oven, poke holes with fork, pour Kahlua over them, let cool.
Do not refrigerate.
Break up frozen candy bars into small pieces (use meat mallet and pound while still in wrappers). If possible, use a 4-quart clear glass bowl so that they layers may be seen.

title: chocolate doughnuts
directions: In a saucepan over hot, but not boiling, water, melt the unsweetened chocolate with 2 tablespoons sweet butter.
Cool. Meanwhile, beat 3 eggs with sugar and sour milk.
Still beating, add the chocolate and butter mixture.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg or mace; add lemon peel.
Blend the sifted ingredients into the egg mixture; beat a few strokes. Chill the dough for easier handling. Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Roll it out 1-inch thick, handling as little as possible, and cut into rounds with a floured doughnut cutter.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Cover beef with water.
Add other ingredients and cook.
Add 2 cups water when meat is done.
Strain gravy and thicken.
Serve over noodles.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Just before serving, add dressing and toss.

title: quick cornbread
directions: Mix all
dry ingredients.
Add milk and hydrogen peroxide. Beat only
until
smooth.
Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with natural margarine.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull cooked chicken breasts from bones.
Using the broth from your chicken, mix stuffing according to box directions.
Add soups to this mixture and let simmer for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chicken and stir well.
Stir in stuffing crumbs and pour into buttered dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake covered dish about 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and continue to bake just long enough to slightly brown the top (about 15 minutes).

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften before mixing in sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fill 21 or 22 foil baking cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° or 300° for 30 minutes (or 40 minutes) or until light golden brown.
When cool, fill centers with prepared pie filling.

title: hot (and i mean hot) taco sauce
directions: Boil jalapenos, stem and peel.
(Wear gloves when handling hot peppers or be really careful to wash thoroughly after working with them or you'll be sorry.
The seeds are the hottest part of a jalapeno, so if you just can't take really firey foods, leave most of the seeds out.)
Boil green chillies if using fresh ones; peel. Blend all ingredients together in blender or food processor until consistency desired.
(I like it left a little chunky.)
Simmer until volume is reduced somewhat and it thickens, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Freezes well or put in sterilized jars, seal and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook over low heat until forms a soft ball in water or to the soft ball stage on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir until cool.

title: worlds best cookies
directions: Cream sugar, brown sugar, butter, oil, egg and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cream of tarter and add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended. Stir in cereal, oatmeal and nuts.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Flatten with fork, Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: melon cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Rinse the Cornish hens and pat dry. Lift the breast skin of a Cornish hen and rub thyme underneath the skin, and place 1/2 clove of garlic under the skin also. Place a quarter of a lemon inside the breast cavity. Tie the legs up securely with a string. Repeat for the remaining three hens.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and melted butter.
Mix well.
Press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes; sprinkle 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips over crust; top with caramel mix, spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mix; sprinkle with remaining nuts, pressing lightly into top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate.
Cut into bars.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Knead	until smooth soft dough and roll out; cut. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Cut halibut into serving pieces.
Heat shortening in skillet over medium heat.
Mix salt and cornmeal; roll fish in cornmeal mixture.
Place in hot shortening in skillet; fry for 3 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: chocolate raisin clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Blend in sweetened condensed milk. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, salt and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let harden and chill.

title: sleigh bells
directions: Cream butter, then beat in the sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time; beat thoroughly after each addition. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg (no salt is needed because of the salt in the butter).
Mix together honey, vanilla and rum extract.
Add a little at a time to the butter, sugar, egg mixture, alternating with the flour mixture.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
(Do not flour fruit and nuts.) Drop by teaspoonfuls (I use ice tea spoons because it makes a neater cookie) about 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
(Too much grease tends to make the cookies run together.) Bake about 15 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.
Yields about 10 dozen cookies.
Store in cake tins with wax paper between layers of cookies.

title: ginger balls
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add egg and beat well.
Add molasses and sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in balls. Makes nicer cookies if they aren't flattened down.

title: maggie's egg pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour.
Add cooled oleo, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in a 10-inch unbaked crust at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: tea punch
directions: Fill with water to make 1 gallon.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Clean and devein shrimp; place in bowl of ice until ready to use. Saute onions, green peppers, celery and garlic in butter until onion is transparent. Add soups and 1 can of water. Add remaining ingredients. Allow to simmer 20-30 minutes on medium to low heat. Drain and pat shrimp dry and add to sauce. Cook for 5-10 minutes, until completely pink and cooked. Remove bay leaves and serve over rice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with topping.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in medium bowl.
Dip boned chicken in it, then into dry mixture. Place in baking pan coated with margarine. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 1 dozen.
Any fruit may be used in place of raspberries.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 6 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for several hours and serve with tortilla chips.

title: citrus salmon
directions: Place salmon in baking dish, skin side up.
Cut orange and lemon in halves; squeeze half of each and grate rind.

Combine juices and rind; pour over salmon. Sprinkle thyme and pepper. Bake, broil or microwave. Pour pan juices over cooked salmon. Slice remaining fruit for garnish. Bake 10 minutes per inch of thickness at 450°.
Broil 10 minutes per inch of thickness.
(Do not turn.)
Microwave, covered with waxed paper, at 70% for 3 minutes per inch of thickness.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour together.
Pour over rhubarb.
Mix egg, milk and food coloring and add to rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with margarine.
Add a top crust, cut slits on top crust and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Crush wafers fine and put more than half in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Cream butter and mix with sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Spread over crumbs.
Cover with strawberries.
Spread whipped cream over that and then sprinkle wafer crumbs on top of cream.

title: rockwoods chocolate bits brownies
directions: Soften butter.
Beat until creamy and add gradually the 2 sugars.
Beat well, until very light and fluffy.
Add well beaten egg and beat again.
Sift flour with salt and soda and add to flour mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts, then chocolate bits.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: barbecue
directions: Melt together. Boil smoked sausage to get grease out.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: kentucky corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in a greased skillet at 350° for 45 minutes. Freezes well.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Boil macaroni.
Mix corned beef, soups, eggs and spices together.
Layer macaroni, corned beef mixture, then cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with salad and French bread.
Serves 8.

title: uncle fred's chili
directions: Brown 2 pounds of ground beef.
Drain grease and pour cooked beef into a 2-gallon pot.
Add tomato sauce, beans, diced green chilies, chili powder and water.
Mix the ingredients together and stir on low heat.

title: cinnamon cookies(diabetic recipe)
directions: Cream margarine; blend in flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix artificial sweetener with vanilla and milk.
Stir into flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into 30 balls and place on cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yield:
30 cookies. Calories:
4 cookies = 150.
Exchange per serving:
4 cookies = 1 bread, 2 fat.

title: crab mold
directions: Combine gelatin and water, let stand 5 minutes to soften. Pour soup in a 2-quart saucepan, set over medium heat, add the gelatin mixture and cook, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in cream cheese until melted; remove from heat and set aside to cool.

title: quick and easy charolais beef stroganoff
directions: Marinade Charolais T-bone steaks for 2 to 3 hours in a mixture of Worcestershire sauce, corn oil, vinegar, crushed garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook to desired doneness over a charcoal fire, or broil in the oven.

title: quick waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 1 minute.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Makes 10 to 12 waffles.

title: sweet pie dough
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add all other ingredients.
Mold into pie pan with hands and fit into pie pans.
Bake crust at 350° until done.
Will rise and puff some. Will not get real brown.
Add pie filling and return to the oven just long enough for filling to set and flavor to go through pie.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, saving 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until heated.
Put 1/2 cup cheese on top and melt.
Serve.

title: classic zero dressing
directions: Chopped parsley,
garlic, horseradish (unsalted), green pepper and dry mustard may be added, if desired.

title: diabetic raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift dry ingredients together. Add margarine, orange peel, eggs and skim milk, mix until blended. Stir in raisins and nuts. Place in a 3 x 5 x 9 inch well greased loaf pan. Bake one hour and 15 minutes or until loaf test done. Remove from pan, cool and store 12 hours before cutting.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over ribs and bake at 300° at least 2 hours.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wash, peel and cut up apples in small quarters.
Remove seeds. Roll out 2 cans biscuits on dough board.
Place pieces of apples on dough.
Wrap dough tightly around apples.
Put some water in a pot.
Let boil; drop the apple dough in, then put a small amount of milk in and sugar to taste.

title: west indies salad
directions: Put crabmeat and onion in a bowl.
Mix oil, vinegar and ice water (take out ice).
Pour over meat and onion.
Let sit overnight.

title: shrimp spread for canapes
directions: Mix the shrimp, mayonnaise, cheese, curry and onion powder well and spread on the party rye bread.
