Put in the broiler for a few minutes.
Makes enough for 1 package of the party rye.
Can also be spread on crackers.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves together.
Mix well sugar, margarine, egg and molasses.
Add sifted flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Put in bag of powdered sugar.
Shake.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: kansas swiss steak
directions: Mix together dry mustard and flour; rub into steak. Season with salt and pepper to taste; brown steak on both sides in hot fat. Place in small roaster and pour mixture of remaining ingredients over steak. Cover and bake in slow oven (325°) for about 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: corn and yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Melt oleo in dish.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and bacon bits.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with grated cheese and bacon bits.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: ginny's marinated chicken wings
directions: Add all ingredients to Ziploc bag.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 375° for one hour.

title: muesli
directions: Mix the oats and water together.

Mix in squirt of lemon juice, then stir in the cream or milk. Grate the washed, unpeeled apples directly into the oat mixture and stir well. Season to taste with sugar or honey and sprinkle the nuts over each serving. Makes 2 servings. Preparation time:
5 minutes.

title: sunflower loaf
directions: Mix well and let stand 1 hour with a cover on it, then bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: quick southern fried chicken
directions: Preheat cooking oil in deep skillet (enough oil to cover chicken).
Clean and wash chicken.
Season with salts and pepper. Dip chicken into milk; drain.
Then sprinkle with flour.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Place pineapple and sugar in a pan and bring to a boil.
Turn off, then add gelatin, lemon juice, cherries, cherry juice and cream cheese, cut into pieces.
Stir together.
Place in refrigerator until it is set but not real stiff.
Whip the cream to soft peaks.
Then fold together with rest of ingredients.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add marshmallows, stirring until slightly melted.
Stir in pineapple and apricot baby food.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Place jalapenos and onion in blender and mix well.
Add all additional ingredients and mix again.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Serve mixed with Velveeta cheese or sour cream or enjoy plain.

title: "taco dip"
directions: Layer in small glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve warm with Doritos or nacho chips.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cover leaves with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes or until limp.
Drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Place equal portions of meat mixture in center of each leaf.
Fold sides of each leaf over meat.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick or string. Brown in hot Wesson oil.
In a very large skillet put in sauce. Combine sugar, water and lemon juice.
Stir into tomato sauce. Simmer, covered, 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: grape leaves stuffed with cheese
directions: Mix Feta cheese, dill weed and bread crumbs.
Roll about 1 tablespoon of mixture in each leaf.
Arrange leaves, seam down, on buttered baking tray.
Dot leaves with butter and bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese has melted and tops of leaves have begun to brown, ever so slightly.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: mexican fiesta casserole(a meal in a minute)
directions: Will also need one large pot.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Remove the seeds and flatten half of the chilis in a 9 X 13 flat pan.
Grate or slice Cheddar cheese and layer it over chilis. Make a second layer of the remaining chilis as before.
Make a layer of the Jack cheese.
Beat whites of 4 eggs in a bowl.
Beat yolks in a separate bowl.
To the yolks add 1 1/2 tsp. of salt, pepper, and the can of evaporated milk.
Fold this into the whites and pour over chilis and cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Then pour on tomato sauce and bake for 30 more minutes. Makes a lot!

title: garden chicken salad
directions: In small bowl, whisk together first 5 ingredients to make dressing.
In large bowl, toss vegetables with half of salad dressing; arrange on lettuce lined platter.
Top with chicken and serve with remaining dressing.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Top with crushed peppers and Italian seasoning.
Top with sausage, hamburger or pepperoni or whatever you like.
Top with shredded Provolone or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: congo bars
directions: Stir brown sugar and melted butter together.
After mixing all ingredients together, place in greased 1-inch side square pan. Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: harlequin dip
directions: Combine the chopped green chillies with the chopped olives, tomatoes and green onions, the lemon juice, oil, garlic salt and pepper in a medium-size bowl, blending well.
Serve immediately or refrigerate overnight to heighten the flavors.
Hollow out a sweet red pepper, if you wish, and fill with the dip.
Makes 3 cups.

title: basic tart crust
directions: In a small bowl, beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add extract.
Mix again.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen one-inch balls.
Place in tiny ungreased muffin cup.
Can use small paper cups.
Press dough on bottom and sides of cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly in pan.
Remove carefully and cool well.
Fill with desired filling.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim all fat from meat and slice, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put meat in shallow dish and cover with the sauce. Marinate 12 to 24 hours.
Lay strips in single layer over oven rack.
Put cookie sheet below to catch drippings.
Set oven at low temperature, about 150°, with door cracked open.
Roast 6 to 8 hours, testing for chewiness.
Store in glass jar.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package and mix all ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Chop onion, lettuce, tomato and combine with ground beef.
Mix taco spice and Thousand Island dressing.
Add dressing and Cheddar cheese to vegetables and beef mixture.
Before serving, add chips and toss again.
May also use picante sauce.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart Pyrex baking dish or casserole.
Stir together flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into butter.
Stir gently.
Add peaches that have been tossed with remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Bring to a boil the raisins, mincemeat and water. Let cool and add soda. Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs. Combine the two mixtures, then add flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Fold in nuts. Use large tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: dirt pie
directions: Cream together margarine, softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat milk with pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Beat together the cream cheese mixture and the pudding mixture.
Layer together in a flowerpot or bucket, first the crushed Oreos, then the mixture.
Keep layering in that order, ending up with crushed Oreos on top.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Decorate with gummy worms.

title: pear relish
directions: Wash and pare pears; cut in quarters.
Wash and cut open peppers; remove seeds.
Peel onions.
Run pears, peppers and onions through food chopper.
Place in large kettle.
Add sugar, salt, turmeric and spice.
Blend thoroughly.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Pack hot in pints.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in bread.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: island green beans
directions: Mix all together.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well by hand.
Form into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: 12 day sweet cucumber pickles(makes 2 gallons)
directions: Dissolve 4 cups salt to 1 gallon of boiling water.
May take more than 1 gallon to cover.
Pour over 2 gallons of whole cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours and drain.

title: grilled fish fillets
directions: Rinse fillets in cold water, pat dry with paper towel.	Place in center of square of foil, sprinkle both sides with seasoned salt. Wash zucchini and squash, no need to peel.
Cut into 2 to 3 inch sticks.
Slice red pepper to 1/4 inch thickness.
Place vegetables on foil with fish, dribble lemon juice over all.
Put about a tsp. of margarine on top and seal foil with double fold on top and ends.
Pierce foil on top with 2 small holes to vent. Place on hot grill for about 15 minutes, no need to turn.
Cooking time varies according to the thickness of fish and heat of the grill, also whether or not grill has a lid.
Fish can be baked in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pizelles filled with whipped icing
directions: Add and beat ingredients together in order listed.
Drop by rounded spoonful onto center of preheated Pizelle Iron.
Close lid and cook until steaming stops (30-45 seconds).
Remove with fork. While still hot, roll into a cylinder.
Fill with Baker's Whipped Icing (recipe follows) after cooling.
Makes about 36 Pizelles.

title: edward's dinosaur
directions: You will need toothpicks for assembly.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Cook until golden brown.
Place in airtight container when cooled.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onions.
Add remaining ingredients to hamburger; mix well.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add boiling water.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until fluffy.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with water and vanilla.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost..

title: vegetables au gratin
directions: In a wok, saute carrots, broccoli, cauliflower and mushrooms until tender.
Place vegetables in a greased casserole.
In a large skillet, saute butter and onion, then add soup, cheese and salt.
Stir until mixture is smooth on low heat.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: california dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and keep in the refrigerator. Makes 3 cups of salad dressing.

title: joyce's delightful imperial chicken
directions: Dip each piece of chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Lay on baking rack with drip pan (not overlapping). Drizzle with rest of butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (do not turn chicken).

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn; put in greased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion, cheese and salt; spread over top.
Mix melted margarine, almonds and crackers; spread on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be made and refrigerated the night before cooking.

title: heavenly cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl of tolerance until blended.
Pour in favorite mold and serve with generous topping of prayer.
Will keep indefinitely!

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, melted butter and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese and brown sugar and spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with fork.
Stir in pecans and cover well.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over pecan
mixture.
Stir all together.
Put in cookie pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Heat last 3 ingredients; dribble over cake and swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quesadilla quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease bottom of quiche pan.
Sprinkle chilies and cheese over bottom.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add Bisquick and beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies and cheese. Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted at middle comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Top with sour cream and sauce to taste.

title: granola
directions: Mix together.
Bake on cookie sheets at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Boil 10 minutes the sugar, water and garlic.
Take out garlic and add vinegar, catsup, salad oil chopped onion, salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pickled jalapenos
directions: Wash jalapenos and prick each with a needle.
Do not cut stems off.
Pack into pint jars with clove of garlic and 1 teaspoon dill seed per jar.
Mix cider vinegar, water and canning salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour immediately over peppers.
Should be enough for 5 to 6 pints.
Seal and process.

title: punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze. Just before serving, pour in 2 bottles ginger ale or Wink to each gallon of mixture.

title: low-fat breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 9-inch pie plate with low-fat cooking spray.
Mix sausage, onion and cheeses and distribute evenly in pie plate.
Stir Bisquick, milk, pepper and Egg Beaters together until smooth. Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot bundt cake*
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, with spoon, mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In small bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Add egg mixture, shredded carrots and applesauce into flour mixture.
Stir, just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan, spreading evenly.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
With spatula, loosen cake from pan.
Invert onto wire rack to cool completely.

title: lemon-cracker baked fish(spanish mackerel or catfish)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse fish under running water.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Place fish into buttered baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle lightly with salt to taste if desired.
Cook in oven about 15 minutes until fork inserts easily.
Remove from oven.
Cover with and layer around with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and sprinkle lemon juice over all.
Place back in oven and cook until cracker crumbs are lightly browned (about 10 minutes). Do not overbrown.
May serve 4 to 6.

title: england-style bean soup(you can make this soup in less than 20 minutes.)
directions: Cook ham, onion and green pepper in bacon drippings in large skillet until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, water, brown sugar, vinegar and salt.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
(You may have to put into a larger saucepan.) Reserve 1 cup beans from can.
Mash the remainder.
Add reserved and mashed beans to soup.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Makes about 5 cups.
(Serve with a slice of corn bread, lettuce salad, baked apple or other fruit and cookies, with milk to drink. Makes a great meal.)
Quick, too.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Roll dough into 12 x 7-inch oblong.
Spread with butter; sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Roll up, beginning at wide side.
Seal well by pinching dough.
Place sealed edges down in ring on lightly greased baking sheet.
With scissors, make cuts 2/3 of way through at 1-inch intervals.
Turn each section on side.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Frost while slightly warm with powdered sugar frosting.

title: wheatie cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Blend.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add half to creamed mixture.
Cream well, then add other half dry
mixture.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Blend, then add Wheaties.
Mix with a spoon.
Batter will be stiff.
Roll in walnut-size balls.
Place 3-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Check first batch to observe browning time.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.
Delicious!

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out 3/16 inch thick on floured board.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: mango salsa
directions: Peel avocados and mangoes and chop fine in bowl.
Chop cilantro and onions and add to mixture.
If tomatoes are juicy, squeeze out excess juice before chopping and adding.
Add spices to your liking.
Enjoy with tortilla chips.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour a little at a time. Finish mixing by hand.
Add Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscross mashing with a fork.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack. Store in an airtight container.

title: easy meat pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fit pie crust into 9-inch pie pan.
Fill with mixture.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes until brown.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternating, beginning and ending with flour.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan and one 8-inch loaf pan at 300° for 2 hours.
Serves 20.

title: baked squash
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour or until browned on top.

title: sour cream chocolate bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt well in mixer.
Boil margarine, water, cocoa and vanilla; combine with flour/sugar mixture.
Add eggs and sour cream to which has been added soda.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes on greased and floured cookie sheet(15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inches).

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with white sauce and peas.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Pare and dice eggplant.
Cook until tender in boiling water. Drain well and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Chop only finely. Melt 1 tablespoon butter and saute the onion until light brown; add to eggplant.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and stir into it until butter has absorbed cracker crumbs or bread crumbs.
Place layers of eggplant and layers of crumbs in a baking dish.
If crackers are unsalted, add salt and paprika.
Have the top layer crumbs. Pour milk over the top.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form into small balls and place onto cookie sheet.
Press down slightly with fork.
Bake until light brown

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° about 30 minutes or until done.
Spread Marshmallow Creme on warm cake.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together, form into balls, place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or less at 450 degrees.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Prick pie shell and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: cold oven chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine & crisco stick, add eggs & sugar beat until all lumps are gone. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased tube cake pan or 2 loaf pans. Do not preheat oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar. Pour over strawberries. add bananas and cool whip. Stir in pecans and freeze. Great on a really hot day!

title: italian pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, minced onion, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 1 hour to blend flavors before serving.

title: strawberry pie for 10-inch pan
directions: Wash and dry strawberries. Line pastry shell with strawberries, except for 1 cup for glaze.
Crush 1 cup strawberries.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch and sugar. Add to strawberry glaze.
Cook until clear and thick. Cover strawberries. Cool for 2 to 3 hours. Top with whipped cream when ready to serve.

title: cookie pops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spoon dough by tablespoonfuls and shape each into 1 1/2-inch balls.

Arrange in circle on ungreased cookie sheets, 3-inches apart and 2-inches from edges; flatten slightly. Securely insert a wooden stick into each cookie with end pointing toward the center of the cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 11 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Cool 2 minutes; remove from cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: ranch beans
directions: Fry hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat Coke and cherry juice.
Dissolve jello, cream cheese and mayonnaise in mixture.
Add cherries, pineapple and pecans.
Let cool and chill to serve.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk until it bubbles around edges of pan, don't boil. Mix eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla, salt, food coloring and milk. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° until set at edge of pie.
Don't overcook.

title: lemon cream squares
directions: Line baking dish (approximately 9 x 12-inch) with 1 package of rolls.
Mix the next 5 ingredients; spread on crescent rolls.
Top with 1 package of rolls.
Beat egg white and spread over top. Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.
Cool and slice into squares.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring liquids to a boil.
Pour over ingredients while hot.

title: dixie delights
directions: Heat peanut butter and butter slightly to mix.
Transfer to large bowl.
Cream in sugar and dry milk.
Add raisins.
Spread and press into a sheet pan or cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and butter in double boiler, then pour over peanut butter mixture. When cooled, cut into squares (makes 25).

title: cherry-topped icebox cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with some of the graham crackers, breaking crackers, if necessary.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the sugar and cinnamon together in a large bowl.
(You want it to be more of brownish color.)
Melt the butter in another bowl. Cut each biscuit into fourths. Dip each piece into the melted butter, then the sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Place into a Bundt pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Add juice to Jell-O.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling until Jell-O is dissolved.
Remove from heat. Add cranberry sauce, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Add sour cream, pineapple and nuts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: barbecued shrimp diane
directions: In a large skillet over high heat, melt the margarine.
Add the shrimp and saute for 3 minutes, or until the shrimp start to stick to the bottom of the skillet, but stir constantly to prevent burning.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring for 5 minutes longer, or until the sauce thickens.
Serve hot.

title: ground beef barbecue
directions: Preheat
oven
Roll out biscuits 2 at a time. Spoon corned
beef into center of biscuit.
Place onion slice on beef. Add
a
tablespoon
of olives and 3 or 4 strips bell pepper. Place
one slice of cheese over all; top with remaining
biscuit. Flute
around
edges
with
fork.
Repeat
with ingredients. Place in biscuit pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown. Yield:
5 servings.

title: tuna dip
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water for 30 to 60 seconds until skins loosen.
Dip in cold water; slip off skins.
Core and chop tomatoes.
In a 6-quart saucepot, combine tomatoes and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.

title: quick cherry crumble
directions: Pour pie filling into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with cake mix and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve plain or with whip cream or ice cream.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch or flour and salt.
Sprinkle over fruit in 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan; dot with butter and adjust top crust.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add tomatoes, eggs, Miracle Whip, salt and pepper to macaroni. Let set in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin breads
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs and sugar.
Mix well. Stir in pumpkin, oil and water.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon and baking powder.
Pour into greased soup or vegetable cans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake until tester in center is clean, about 50 minutes.
Cool.
Slice.
Makes 4 cups batter to fill 5 soup or 4 vegetable cans.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add cream cheese and stir until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, dissolved in water and then add remaining ingredients.
Beat until texture is smooth.
Set in refrigerator until it sets.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender; drain and mash.
Then add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and put in a baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl with fork.
Roll in nuts, then cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: raspberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Combine eggs, oil and sugar; mix.
Add dry ingredients; mix and add berries.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kosher slaw
directions: Alternate cabbage, onions and pepper in large bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/8 cup of the sugar.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard, celery seed and oil to boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
When cool, pour into another bowl and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Rub shortening into flour with sugar, baking powder, baking soda and a pinch of salt.
Add well beaten egg, buttermilk, raisins and caraway seed.
Knead on a floured board and bake in a round glass casserole dish with cross cut in top of dough.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Delicious served warm with butter and jams.
Truly an Irish tradition!

title: yummy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut up butter into a sheet cake baking pan.
Place in oven to melt.
Take pan from oven.
Sprinkle in cracker crumbs.
In a small bowl pour condensed milk and add peanut butter, stir.
Spoon this on top of crumbs.
Now sprinkle granola around over this.
Next, sprinkle chocolate chips and cover top with coconut.
Pat down with your hand.
Place in oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.
Then cut into bars.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs separately and add; mix well.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 40 minutes or until firm.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients well with an electric mixer.

title: lemon butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, lemon rind, lemon juice, cinnamon, powdered cloves, salt and flour.
Add more flour, if necessary, to make dough thick enough to roll.
Chill, then roll.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage in boiling water to soften leaves, they work better.
Mix ingredients together.
Put mixture on cabbage leaves, roll up and secure with toothpicks and cook in tomato juice about 1 hour on medium heat or until tender.

title: hash brown casserole 1
directions: Mix everything except hash browns.
Then add hash browns, salt, and pepper.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: liver and peppers venetian style
directions: Put onion halves flat side down on board and slice long narrow strips from root to stem.
Cook onion and bacon in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes until onion is lightly browned and bacon is crisp.
Meanwhile, sprinkle liver with flour; toss to coat.
Remove onion mixture with slotted spoon.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings from skillet.
Put liver in skillet, stirring often with a fork to separate pieces.
Cook for 8 minutes or until browned.
Add oregano, pepper, vinegar and water; stir to blend.
Add onion-bacon mixture and roasted peppers.
Stirring occasionally, cook for 4 minutes until hot and sauce has thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, heat butter, onion, salt, celery salt, pepper and milk just to boiling. Stir in Potato Puffs (dry); continue cooking until smooth. Stir constantly. Garnish with cheese, bacon, sour cream, chives, paprika and parsley.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water and refrigerate until partially set.
Take partially set Jell-O and beat about a minute. Then add 1/2 of the Cool Whip and beat, then mix in well drained pineapple.
Place this mixture in a 13 x 9-inch serving dish. Place marshmallows on top.

title: 45 minute spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until light brown, pouring off excess fat.
Add onions and ground chuck.
Cook, stirring with fork, until brown.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, Worcestershire, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add olives; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix cheese, flour, Accent and salt.
Cut in the butter. Sprinkle with water and form dough with fork.
Roll into a log, wrap in wax paper and chill 2 hours.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Cook and stir green beans and mushrooms in butter in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk, broth and reserved mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken; heat until hot.
Serve over white rice or white toasted bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Blend hash browns, margarine, onion, soup, pepper and cheese. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes, mixed with melted butter.
Put over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nippy tuna casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine over low heat until tender. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Spoon half each of corn, eggs, tuna, sauce and cheese into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Repeat layers, reserving 1/2 cup of cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Stir until smooth batter appears.
Grease skillet or griddle lightly with oil.
Heat until a few drops of water sizzles when dropped on surface.
Pour batter to form pancake on griddle or skillet.
When batter starts to bubble, flip pancake and brown other side.
Serve with butter and syrup. Makes about six pancakes.
Double ingredients for large family.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans evenly in bottom of well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter; heat to dissolve, then pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove to serving plate.

title: potato pizza
directions: Place 4 cups sliced potatoes in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread finely chopped onion over potatoes, salt and pepper lightly.
Prepare sauce by combining soup, milk, tomato paste, oregano, garlic and sugar.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add the egg and molasses; beat thoroughly.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture alternately with the boiling water.
Beat after each addition.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in moderate oven at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm; top with cream (whipped cream, Cool Whip or Dream Whip may be used).

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil
carrots just until tender; add other ingredients. Let marinate overnight.
Will keep for several days.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle.
Beat egg until light and fluffy; add milk. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to egg-milk mixture; beat until smooth.
Stir in oleo and fold in blueberries.
Serves 4 to 5.
Try with Blueberry Syrup!

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook berries with sugar until partially done.
Cool slightly. Pour berries with juice in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the dry yellow cake mix over the berries and juice.
Cover with thin slices of oleo or butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: leslie lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, pork sausage, garlic and onion in a large saucepan.
Drain off all fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, parsley, sugar, salt and spices.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until sauce is the consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce into baking pan and alternate with layers of noodles, grated cheese, Mozzarella, spoonfuls of Ricotta cheese and tomato sauce until all ingredients are used.
Top layer should be sauce and grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together the margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Sift the flour and salt together and stir into the margarine mixture. Stir in the nuts.
Chill the dough, then roll into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven until set, but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Let them cool, then roll in sugar again.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Bake at 300° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's pie dough
directions: Blend flour and shortening together.
In small bowl, mix remaining ingredients and roll out.

title: dill pickled okra
directions: Use small tender pods of okra; cut with as much stem as possible.
Wash and drain.
Prick okra and pack in clean jars. Place in a small bunch of dill in jar.
Boil water, vinegar and salt together.
Fill jars with hot brine.
Put on cap.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Drain.
Press out.
Mix vinegar and sugar together and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers and place in small freezer containers until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl with a fork until crumbly.
Dump into ungreased 13 x 9 inch pan and press firmly into even layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put a layer of lettuce, peas, tomato, onion, cheese and bacon. Mix mayonnaise
and
sugar for dressing.
Put dressing on last. (Best to put dressing on 1 hour before serving.)

title: handy casserole
directions: Put a layer of browned hamburg in an ovenproof dish.
Over this, put a layer of sliced potatoes (cooked until about soft), then add a layer of canned vegetables (your choice).
Add soup; top with cheese layer over all and cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole(yield: 4 servings; cooking time: 25 to 30 minutes)
directions: Melt cheese in evaporated milk, using low heat (may microwave).
Fry ground beef until browned, using medium heat. Add salt and garlic salt.
Fry tortillas using medium-high heat in 1/2-inch shortening on each side only until soft.

title: lemon nut crunch cake
directions: Beat Crisco, oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
While still beating, slowly add warm milk; continue beating until sugar is well blended.

title: steak and shrimp kabobs
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen. In a small saucepan combine ketchup, water, chopped onion, brown sugar, lemon juice, oil, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring once or twice. On 6 skewers thread the steak pieces alternating with shrimp, zucchini, corn, onion wedge, and pepper squares. Grill kabobs over medium to hot coals for 15 to 20 minutes or desired doneness. Turn the kabobs often and brush with sauce. Garnish the end of each of the skewers with a cherry tomato before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Spray large pot with cooking spray; brown onions and meat. Add other ingredients and simmer for two hours.
Add water to desired consistency.
Serve with spaghetti noodles or as sauce in lasagne.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: three bean salad
directions: In large bowl, mix with fork
the vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard and pepper.
Add celery and onions.
Then add beans and mix well.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream Margarine, Crisco and Sugar together.
Add Molasses and Egg; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto foiled lined cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350 for 10 - 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven!
Combine oleo, butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Place pan in cold oven. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: green pea and cheese salad
directions: Combine peas, cheese and onion.
Toss with mayo and mustard. Chill.
Serve over greens.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Cooking Time:
15 minutes (broil for 5 minutes).
Temperature: 450°.

title: diet lemon delight
directions: Mix together the sugar-free lemon Jell-O and boiling water. Put juice of 1 lemon in measuring cup. Fill up with cold water to make 3/4 cup. Add this to the Jell-O mixture. Chill mixture until it starts to jell.
Mix yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Whip this mixture with partially jelled Jell-O mixture.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square cake pan and chill until firm.

title: zola's "eels of trasimento"(seen in italy at christmastime)
directions: Chop almonds fine with a large, sharp knife, or do in a food processor.
Mix sugar with chopped almonds and then add citron (cut up candied citron).
Next, add lemon or orange peel (the candied kind).
Add 4 to 6 egg whites and mix until holds together well.

title: leatha's sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift 1 cup flour.
Add soda, baking powder and nutmeg to flour.
Stir into shortening and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream and the rest of the flour. Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.

title: skillet creole cabbage
directions: Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet.
Add other ingredients. Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until tender; do not overcook. Yields 8 servings.

title: fiesta zucchini
directions: Heat oil in heavy medium skillet over medium-low heat.
Add zucchini, garlic and oregano and saute until just golden, about 2 minutes.
Add salsa and simmer until zucchini is just tender, about 6 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Sprinkle cheese over zucchini.
Cover and cook until cheese melts, about 2 minutes. Yield: 4 servings.

title: island banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat bananas, brown sugar, milk, oil and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened.
Fold in nuts, coconut and pineapple.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups (cups will be very full).
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spicy liver ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except olives and 1/3 of cream cheese. Form into a ball.
Add a little milk to 1/3 cream cheese; beat until smooth enough to spread.
Spread on ball.
Slice olives; dot on ball.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with small rye bread slices.

title: lemon pie
directions: Squeeze the juice from the two lemons.
Stir in the Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk until the mixture becomes thick. Pour this into the graham cracker pie crust and add the Cool Whip topping.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
May refrigerate until ready to serve.
Then heat at 350° in quiche dish or glass Pyrex for approximately 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles and it browns a little.
Serves 6.
Recipe may be tripled for amounts.
Serve with chips or crackers.
One-half cup sour cream can be substituted for 1/2 cup of the mayonnaise.

title: mexican burgers(delicious!)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into patties and cook in large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Makes 4 to 6 burgers, depending on size and thickness desired. Serve on lite hamburger buns.
Recipe makes 6 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: beef tips
directions: Cut meat into cubes, oh yeah, remove all fat.
Brown meat. Chop up onions; brown them separately.
Put meat in kettle with liquid and put in oven to cook while you are working on onions. Oh yeah, add a little water.

title: rolling in dough
directions: Put water in large mixing bowl.
Sprinkle yeast on top of water and let dissolve.
Add sugar, salt and about half the flour. Beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually add remaining flour.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Put in refrigerator. Will keep a week or let rise and make rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Melt butter in a heavy ovenproof skillet.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into hot pan of butter; stir until heated. Put skillet in 350° oven and bake.
When crusted around edge and top, turn under and let the crust form again.
Do this twice, allowing the last to remain on sides and top, about 40 minutes. Serve with sweetened cream, ice cream or serve alone.

title: super sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, vegetable oil and granulated sugar in large bowl. Beat until creamy. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs. Mix well. Sift flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar together; add to other ingredients. Mix well. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and cook on stove top 20 minutes.
Cook 8 ounces of spaghetti.
Mix all together and cook 15 more minutes on stove top.
Put in casserole dish and put shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Place in oven until cheese melts. Freezes well.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over pudding and jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add oranges.
When set, add Cool Whip.
Chill thoroughly.

title: low calorie dip
directions: Pour one envelope of either soup mix and a container of sour cream substitute into a large bowl.
Stir well.
Let soup soften. When ready, use as a dip with raw vegetables or low calorie crackers, etc.
You can also spice up a plain sandwich using this instead of mayonnaise.
Contains 19 calories per tablespoon of dip.
tags: container Slender Choice sour cream substitute

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and nuts and set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients with mixer.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crumb mixture over the top.
Bake one hour at 350°. Serve with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated up to two weeks.

title: thad's broccoli pie(pastry or vegetable dish)
directions: Separate biscuits in half by layers.
Line bottom of ungreased 8 x 8-inch baking pan with 1/2 or more biscuits.
Push together to completely line pan.
Fill pan with fresh chopped broccoli.
Cover with 4 slices of American cheese.
Sprinkle with dill weed and garlic powder.
Top with remaining halved biscuits.
Bake according to Big Country directions.
If biscuits are doughy in the middle, bake additional 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a roasting pan.
Fry bacon crisp and when cool, crumble into bean mixture.
Also, pour bacon grease into mixture if you have no fat problem.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Add melted buter last.
If mixture is too thick, add more milk, tablespoons at a time.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: alberta toomey's feather light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Add butter, sugar, salt and mashed potatoes to potato water.
When potato mixture cools, stir in yeast.
Add eggs.
Then add flour enough to make stiff dough.
(Knead.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sugar, then peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and freeze.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, red pepper and onion into bite size pieces. Add raisins and seeds.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture and mix well.

title: chicken dressing dish
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Pour soup over cheese.
Top with dressing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: greek pork pockets
directions: Prepare first 5 ingredients and pour over pork.
Refrigerate for 1 to 8 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes. Beat Crisco until creamy.
Gradually add sugars until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well and form into bite size balls. Store in refrigerator.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in two 13 x 9-inch pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain linguine; cut up tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Add 12 ounces of Robusto Italian dressing; mix well. Sprinkle Italian seasoning packet on top.
Let set 24 hours in fridge.
Before serving, pour in rest of dressing and mix well.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter over medium heat.
Add shredded cabbage and seasonings.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then pineapple and bread cubes.
Add whipping cream last.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars and marshmallows in 2 cups milk on low heat. Add 2 cans Pet Milk; mix well.
Pour in freezer.
Finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water. Mix in all other ingredients. Combine and chill.

title: ma's ripe tomato catsup
directions: Boil until becomes thick, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: simple punch
directions: Mix all together in gallon container.
Chill before serving. Serve with ice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together, then fold in Cool Whip, strawberries and nuts.
Put in pie crust.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour mixture into baking dish (about 9 x 13-inch).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: powdered sugar glaze
directions: Place Splenda and cornstarch in blender jar. Cover and blend until Splenda is a very fine powder. Pour into a small bowl. Add water and stir well. This recipe makes a thick glaze. Add more water for a thinner glaze.

title: cherry angel cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4 inch slices on bottom of 13 x 9 inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract.
Mix well.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half cream mixture over cake slices.
Top with 1 can pie filling.
Top with remaining cake slices, cream mixture and pie filling.
Chill 4 hours until set.

title: green tomato pie(two crust pie)
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Fill lined pie pan with slices. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Try it.
It's really good.

title: busy day hamburgers
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in flour.
Add soup and stir well. Cook several minutes.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Garnish with pickle, relish, catsup or mustard.

title: art's hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and nuts and set aside.
Combine wet ingredients and stir by hand until well mixed.
DO NOT BEAT. Fold liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
DO NOT BEAT.
Pour into greased cake pan, cover with a fine layer of bread crumbs. Bake at 325 degrees for 40-45 minutes until done.
Do not overbake.

title: choco-dot cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, shortening, butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Press 3 to 4 extra candies in cookies, if desired.
Bake until light brown for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from sheets.

title: colorado chili
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium-high heat, brown meat on all sides in 1 teaspoon oil; drain. Remove meat and keep warm. In the same pan, saute the onion, celery, jalapeno and garlic in remaining oil until tender. Stir in the water, chili powder, brown sugar, cumin, salt and pepper. Return meat to pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in the tomato paste, beans and tomatoes. Return to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes longer or until meat is tender and beans are heated through. Garnish with cilantro. Yield: 5 servings.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz, onion and crab meat; spread over English muffins.
Cut into 1/4 or 1/2-inch wedges.
Broil a few minutes.

title: ham and chili cheese ball
directions: In a small bowl, combine cheeses, deviled ham, onions and chilies.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill.
Soften slightly before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Makes a 2 cup cheese ball.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together until smooth; pour into greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn off oven after 1 hour.
Leave door ajar and leave cheesecake in oven for another hour cooling.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onion.
Melt cheese; add water, taco seasoning, Pet milk and Ro-Tel.
Mix well.
Add beef and onion.
Heat and serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling salted water according to package directions until tender but still firm; drain.
Meanwhile beat egg in a medium-size bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, the turkey ham, parsley, oregano and pepper.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over bottom of an 11 1/2 x 7 3/4-inch baking dish.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons cottage cheese mixture into each shell.
Arrange in baking dish in single layer.
Top with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Take out of oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand uncovered 7 minutes to melt cheese.

title: ham delights
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Use sharp knife to cut rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread mustard mixture on top and bottom of rolls.
Add cheese and ham.
After replacing top, cut into individuals and heat 20 minutes at 350°, wrapped in foil.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cheese until soft; blend in mayonnaise.
Mix in pineapple, pecans, marshmallows and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: cooked pimento and cheese
directions: Melt cheese in milk, slowly.
Cool.
Add vinegar, eggs, sugar and pimento; beat together.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Cool; add mayonnaise.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and salt in small amount of water until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Melt butter or oleo and mix herb dressing together. Put 1/2 of herb dressing in bottom of baking dish.
Add squash mixture.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-grapefruit salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Set aside.
Just before serving, combine salad greens and remaining ingredients.
Drizzle with dressing and toss gently.

title: purple plum cobbler
directions: Drain and pit plums, saving 1/2 cup syrup. Heat syrup with sugar and lemon juice until it comes to the boil. Turn into a shallow baking dish and add plums. Combine remaining ingredients and mix to a soft dough. Drop by spoonfuls onto the plum mixture. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jiffy hominy bake
directions: *(I use dry onion flakes instead of fresh.)

title: chocolate ravioli cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Melt chocolate and cool.
Beat in egg, chocolate and baking powder with mixer on low speed, beat in flour just until blended.
Pat dough into a disk, wrap in plastic wrap, refrigerate 1 hour until firm enough to shape and roll out. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough on lightly floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch squares.
Spoon 1 heaping teaspoon cherry pie filling in center.
Brush edges with beaten egg white.
Top with remaining square (dough may crack slightly). Press edges with fork to seal.
With a sharp knife, cut an X in the center of tops.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes. Makes about 18.

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter.
When melted, put the other ingredients in.
Pour beef consomme on the top.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: caraway onion quick bread
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in cereal and buttermilk.
Let stand for 2 minutes or until the cereal softens and most of the liquid is soaked up. Beat in the egg.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl.
Form into ball and wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: salmon bisque
directions: Combine in blender salmon, tomatoes, onion, parsley and chicken stock.
Simmer this for 20 minutes.
In separate pan, melt butter.
Add flour and stir in milk.
Add salt and paprika.
Add milk mixture to salmon mix once it's smooth and boiling.
Do not let bisque boil.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Layer 1:
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix according to directions. Cool and crumble in long Pyrex dish.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish and sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: country-style strawberry ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Slowly add sugar and beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Pour into can of ice cream freezer, add strawberries and milk to fill line, if needed.
Freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: bacon vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 5 hours. Best when made one day before use to allow flavors to combine. Yields 1 cup.

title: lemon (or lime) meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add hot water and cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat; add egg yolks to part of mixture.
Blend with rest of mixture.
Stir and cook over low heat about 6 minutes longer.
Remove from stove; add juice and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Make meringue.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and paprika. Pour into "Pammed" casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake
at
for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: ed's fudge(chocolate fudge)
directions: Combine all the chips and Eagle Brand milk in a glass bowl. Stir until mixed. Microwave on HIGH for 3 minutes. Remove from microwave and stir until smooth. Add vanilla and nuts and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that is lined with waxed paper. Chill in refrigerator until firm. Turn out on cutting board. Remove waxed paper and cut into desired size pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil the fryer and debone.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Saute oleo, onion and celery.
Add pimentos and soup.
Mix with spaghetti and put into a casserole.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: microwave carrot cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Mix flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; blend into egg mixture.
Fold in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a greased 9-inch microwave-safe tube pan. Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto cake plate and let cool completely.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture gradually and blend well.
Form into balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and place candy Kisses on top; bake for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: party onions
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese in a small bowl; set aside.
Wash and trim onions.
Cover white
onion bulbs with cream cheese mixture.
Roll coated bulbs in Cheddar cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, blending thoroughly.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda, beating until well blended.

title: anise biscotti
directions: Into large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
With spoon stir in remaining 1 cup of flour.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap, refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
(or place dough in freezer for 30 minutes)

title: corn pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine crumbs and melted butter. Reserving about 1/2 cup, press remainder into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
Mix 1 cup of the milk, corn, salt, pepper and onion in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Blend flour into remaining milk and add to the corn mixture, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add some sauce to the beaten eggs and add it back to the pan, stirring well to mix thoroughly.
Pour the corn into the prepared crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs; dust with paprika and bake 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together egg, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar using a fork or whisk slightly to beat together. Add One Minute oatmeal; mix with other ingredients.
Add hamburger meat using your hands.
Add A.1.
Steak sauce using your hands once again.
Place prepared mixture in an ungreased loaf pan.
Put ketchup on top to decorate.
Place in oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix vegetables with salt and pepper.
Cover 2-quart casserole with crackers.
Spread vegetables over crackers.
Spread mayonnaise over vegetables.
Alternate layers, ending with crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: white sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice and mint in 2 large pitchers; cover and refrigerate for 2 hours to blend flavors. Serve over ice.
Garnish with mint sprigs.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and rinse.
In 13 x 9-inch dish, layer lettuce, spinach, tortellini, tomatoes and green onions.
Pour dressing evenly over top; sprinkle bacon evenly over top.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and cream well. Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix and spoon in unbaked shell. Bake in preheated oven 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm and set in the middle.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place leg quarters in large baking dish.
Salt to taste.
Top with butter.
Mix both cans of soup with water; stir in rice and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: dried beef symphony
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
In it, frizzle the beef until crispy.
Sprinkle flour on and mix.
Add sour cream and wine.
Add cheese and finally the artichoke hearts.
Keep warm until serving time.
Spoon over muffins, toast or noodles.
Serves 4.
Ten minutes to prepare.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl in order given.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cup flour, sugar, soda and salt. Mix well. Add butter. Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping. Set aside. Press mixture onto bottom of 13 X 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes. Top crust with chocolate chips. Mix together topping and 1/4 cup flour until smooth. Drizzle over chocolate chips. Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture. Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until golden. Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl mix baking powder, salt, 3 cups cake flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon corn oil spread for topping.
With pastry blender or two knives used scissor fashion, cut in remaining corn oil spread until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk, vanilla and egg until flour is just moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Spoon batter into loaf pan.
Coarsely chop almonds.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Toss together the hash browns, onions and cheese until evenly mixed.
Set aside.
Mix the sour cream, cornstarch, salt, pepper, and thyme.
Add the milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour the liquid mixture over the potato mixture and stir until mixed.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, which is about 50 minutes.
Freezes well.
Reheat in microwave oven for "good as first time" leftovers.

title: easy cherry cobbler
directions: Ingredients will be layered, no mixing, in greased baking dish:

title: cheese breakfast pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Let set for about 10 minutes before slicing.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Set shrimp aside after peeling.
Pout oil or margarine, onions and 1/2 cup chopped celery into a heavy pot.
Season to taste. Cook slowly, uncovered, until onions are wilted.
Finely chop lobster and boiled shrimp.
Mix with onion mixture and cook 15 minutes over medium heat, uncovered.
Add buns which have been soaked in eggs, mix well.
Add bell peppers, remaining celery, green onion tops, parsley and crumbs or meal.
Mix well.
Split each shrimp lengthwise, almost to the end and flatten out.
Stuff centers of split shrimp with mixture, holding each shrimp in the hand and squeezing together to form a croquette.
Roll in flour, then dip in egg batter made up of 2 beaten eggs, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and pinch of salt.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry rapidly 5 minutes in deep fat at 375°.
Serves 5. Delicious.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add nuts to mixture or make a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in cream.
Pour into molds or muffin tins and freeze.

title: homesteaders casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with mashed potatoes.
Spread with cottage cheese on top of potatoes (do not mix).
Place sausage on top of cheese, then place green beans on sausages.
Repeat layering process twice (can add extra layers for larger amounts). Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until the size of small peas or crumbly.
Add together water, egg and vinegar.
Stir with fork. Pour over flour mixture.
Stir until all is moistened.
Make 5 flat balls or patties.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Roll dough on floured cloth.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut cauliflower, broccoli and celery in bite-size pieces.
Add onion rings and mix with cauliflower, broccoli and celery. Scatter peas on top.
Pour dressing over top.
Seal and let stand 24 hours.
Mix well before serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cook artichokes until tender.
Beat drained artichokes with an electric mixer until they are in small pieces.
Add cheese, butter and garlic powder.
Mix and serve warm with crackers.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Grind nuts very fine.
Beat egg yellows.
Add sugar and beat. Add
nuts
and
mix.
Beat egg whites and fold into nut mixture. Bake
in
two
layers at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise together.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with the chopped vegetables and press them firmly into the dressing mixture. Sprinkle with the cheese and refrigerate until serving.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces.
Dip ribs in flour and brown on all sides in 1 tablespoon fat or drippings.
Then remove excess fat, leaving 1/4 cup.
To this add all ingredients.
Cover; simmer at 220° for about 1 1/2 hours, turning once or twice.

title: snow cream
directions: Stir together and serve immediately.
Can add fruit (drained), crushed pineapple or bananas, mashed, etc.

title: peanut butter rice krispies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a pot.
Heat until it comes to a little boil.
Take the pot off of the stove and add in the peanut butter. Stir in quickly.
Pour mixture over rice krispies.
Mix well.
Dump mix into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Gently press and spread out in the pan.

title: pumpkin doughnuts
directions: Combine yeast and sugar and dissolve in 1/4 cup water.
Mix scalded milk, lard or cooking oil, sugar and mashed pumpkin. Pumpkins should have about the same consistency as mashed potatoes. Mix all together and cool.
Add eggs, salt and flour.
Put in large greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll out and cut with doughnut cutter.
Deep fry. Makes 80 doughnuts.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix milk and pineapple well; add enough Crush to fill freezer. Can use other flavors of soda for different taste.

title: choco mint snappers
directions: Melt chocolate chips in the microwave.
Combine shortening, sugar and egg.
Blend in chocolate and Karo syrup.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in gradually.
You may have to chill for a little while to make it easy to shape into balls.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° or until the cookie looks cracked on top.
Bake with oven rack in the middle or at the top level in oven.
If you bake them too close to the burner, the bottoms of the cookies will burn.

title: "cool summer salad"(cucumber and lime jello salad)
directions: Blend together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Peel and grate cucumber into cheese mixture.
Scrape small onion into cheese mixture also and put into jello dissolved in hot water.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five minute cabbage
directions: Heat the milk and cook the cabbage in it for 2 minutes.
Add the cream, flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook rapidly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir constantly.
The cabbage will retain its crispness and is delicate in flavor and color.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop together cabbage and green pepper.
Then grate carrots. Stir in vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add celery seed, if desired.

title: angel salad
directions: Fix jello as directed.
Let partially set.
Stir in pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and let it set.
Better if it sets overnight.

title: martha pafford's coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Use glass pie plate for better results. Chill and serve.

title: health food mix
directions: Mix all together.
Amounts are to taste.

title: crustless quiche(ham or crab)
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms; drain on paper towels.
In blender, put eggs, sour cream, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, flour, salt and hot sauce.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Pour into a large bowl and add crab meat or ham.
Pour into a 10-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less, until firm when shaken.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Wash and peel potatoes, then slice thinly.
Combine onion flakes, flour, salt and pepper; set aside.
Layer potatoes and sprinkle each layer with the dry ingredients, then dot each layer with butter.

title: crunchy oven french toast
directions: Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In shallow bowl, combine eggs, half and half, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.

title: freda's bisquick mix(make your own bisquick mix)
directions: Mix until like corn meal.
Makes 13 cups.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, egg, salt and pineapple juice and cook until thick.
Cool and pour over mixed fruit.
Garnish with chopped pecans and maraschino cherries.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.
Stir pudding mixes into milk in medium saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Place plastic wrap on surface of filling.

title: grandma nancy's baked beans
directions: Wash beans.
Place all ingredients into a crock-pot.
Mix well.
Cook on low overnight for about 16 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add milk, water, soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Mix in rice and zucchini.
Pour into casserole dish, top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until cornbread seems done.

title: easy liver pate
directions: Mash liverwurst.
Blend in with Margarine, Worcestershire, green onion and bacon.
Turn out on wax paper.
Form in 5 x 3 rectangle, Chill half hour.
Spread top and sides with cream cheese.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower; drain well.

title: tex-mex skillet meal
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown, not hard; drain grease, if any.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and water; bring to a boil and add uncooked rice to mixture.
Return to boil and simmer a few minutes, 2 or 3.
Add corn and stir and heat.
Remove from heat and top with cheese.
Cover and let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugars.
Add flour, salt, soda, vanilla and eggs all together.
Mix well on low speed of mixer.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix just enough to mix chips evenly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry in skillet hamburger, onions and chili seasoning until meat is done and onions are tender.
Cover the bottom of a casserole dish with tortilla chips and top with the meat mixture.
Next, layer in the order of mushroom soup, chili beans, tomatoes and green chilies and then cheese.
Put another layer using same order. Bake at 350° or until bubbly and the cheese is melted.

title: impossible quiche(low cholesterol)
directions: Mix in blender the Egg Beaters, Bisquick and milk.
In 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish spread broccoli, onion and cheese. Pour liquid over veggies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham treats
directions: Place graham crackers on foil lined cookie sheet. Sprinkle nuts on top of crackers.
Combine margarine and sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over nuts.
Bake 15 minutes in a 325° oven.
Break apart and serve.

title: apple casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers of sweet potato and apple slices in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle each layer with instant minced onion and salt.
Combine syrup, cider and melted butter; pour over all.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Arrange sausages on top and bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes longer, or until sausages are brown and tender.

title: super salsa dip
directions: Soften cheese in a bowl with electric mixer on low speed until smooth. Add salsa. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Put in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box and pour over coconut and pecans.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Pour over cake mix.
Swirl with knife.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine bread and milks; let stand 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In blender, combine 2 bananas with eggs, cottage cheese, honey, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour excess milk off bread and add to blender.
Puree at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add to bread mixture.
Slice 1 banana, add to bread mixture and stir.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish with nonstick spray.
Put banana mixture into dish.
Set baking dish into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan and pour boiling water into pan to a depth of about 1 inch.
Bake 45 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove pan from baking dish and let cool 10 minutes.
Serve warm or cool completely.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 6.
Contains 216 calories, 3 gm fat and 294 mg sodium.

title: asparagus fried(asparagi fritta)
directions: Cut
off
tough
asparagus ends.
Soak in cold water to remove any sand.
Drain and rinse again.
Cut a 1-inch slit up the center
of each stem.
Bring 1 quart of salted water to a boil and
cook
on steaming rack or upright in asparagus pan. When just
tender,
7 to 9 minutes, depending on size, drain. Whisk eggs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper in shallow bowl; set aside. When
asparagus
are cool to touch, split asparagus at cut.
Dip split asparagus in flour and then into beaten eggs. Bunching
2 to
halves
together;
fry in hot oil in large skillet
until lightly
golden
on each side.
Place on paper towel
to
drain and
then
onto
serving
platter.
Sprinkle lightly with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: german nut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.
Before completely cool, dust with powdered sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, water and salt.
Cool thoroughly.
Drain vegetables.
Mix with dressing.
Chill several hours.
Just before serving, drain off most of the liquid.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard (mix salt and mustard together first to keep from lumping).
Place cubed bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble sausage over bread, then top with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until eggs set.

title: layered salad
directions: Start with layer of lettuce, then one of cauliflower. Sprinkle with bacon and sugar.
Spread dressing on top and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, toss salad well.

title: weight watchers trifle pineapple
directions: Cube cake; pour 1/2 of pineapple over cake.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Pour over cake.
Top with remaining pineapple.
Spread whipped topping on top.
Use a 13 x 7 x 2-inch dish.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar. By hand stir in pumpkin, flour, cinnamon, ginger, salt and baking powder.
Line cookie sheet with wax paper.
Pour batter out thin and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: To present this salad, serve in a clear glass bowl.
Layer vegetables in order, topped with mayonnaise, so all sides are sealed.
Spread grated cheese on top.
When ready to serve, sprinkle croutons on top.
This salad is best when made a day ahead.
Enjoy!!

title: carrot apple salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cut the shortening into the flour until coarse crumbs form. Add the buttermilk, tossing with a fork until a dough forms. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead lightly a few times, just until smooth. Pat dough to 3/4 inch thick. Cut out biscuits with a biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put tomatoes and green chilies in blender and a jalapeno pepper.
Blend 1 minute slowly.
Add cubes of Velveeta.
Heat in heavy saucepan.
Serve with Doritos.

title: oatmeal sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and flour together.
Combine sifted dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and add vanilla last.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake in 350° oven on greased sheet until cookies are browned.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil; add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites that have been stiffly beaten.
Bake at 350° in 3 layers until done.
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
