Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 4 and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top, then nuts. Drizzle melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.
Makes 12 servings.

title: betty's soft tacos
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Add refried beans.
Mix together.
Put mixture in tortillas.
Add lettuce, tomatoes and picante sauce.

title: fruit tart
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl with a mixer.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Arrange sliced fruit on top.
Chill or freeze.
Do not freeze with the fruit on it.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mix in same way you work biscuits and make a biscuit and mash it over your cake pan real thin.
Cook until brown at 350°.
Make 4 layers.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and condensed milk until well blended. In another bowl, combine Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts; add to milk mixture and mix well.
Pour into cooled pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut, green pepper, onion and pimiento. Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Stir in oil, mixing well.
Pour over kraut mixture; toss to mix.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool and remove from bones.
Grind or chop chicken.
Chop celery and pickles.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients well.
Make approximately 2 quarts. Serves 25 people.

title: london chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter, then brown mushrooms.
Place chicken in large casserole.
Mix soup (undiluted and wine).
Pour over chicken.
Place mushrooms on top.
Refrigerate.
When ready to bake, add a little more wine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: arroz con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: Shake Adobo on chicken parts and rub in well.
Brown chicken in oil in large heavy skillet.
Add sofrito and alcaparrado.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add Sazon, water, cube.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Cut pineapple sherbet in chunks and place in punch bowl.
Add chilled 7-Up; serve.
You can double this as many times as needed. Serve with white or yellow cake.

title: creole cabbage
directions: In a big iron skillet, saute yellow onion in bacon drippings. Add all other ingredients except cabbage and simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf and cloves.
Cut cabbage in serving wedges, leaving enough of the core to hold head together.
Boil 10 minutes.
Put cabbage in serving dish.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle with cheese.

title: buttermilk brownies(texas sheet cake)
directions: In saucepan, melt the oleo and cocoa.
Add water and bring to boil.
Pour over the flour, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Mix well, then add the buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet, with sides, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake.

title: supreme chocolate cream pie filling
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Immediately spoon into pie shell and spread the meringue on hot pie filling.
Spread meringue to edge of pastry.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
To prevent meringue shrinkage, move to draft free place. Do not refrigerate.

title: yellow summer squash casserole
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter or margarine, 1/2 cup of bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into well-greased Pyrex dish.

title: sweet potato deluxe
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with sugar, eggs, milk, butter and spices. Bake in a greased casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada squares
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown; drain off fat.
Spread beef in bottom of a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Beat eggs, milk, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce mix.
Pour over beef; sprinkle with olives.
Top with corn chips.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: ham loaf with brown sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into 16 individual rolls.
Place in well-greased pan.
Baste with Brown Sauce every 30 minutes. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hand rolled butter cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and break off into small pieces. Roll in palms of hands.
Curl if desired into shapes.
Bake in oven at 375° until light brown. Roll on powdered sugar while still warm.

title: cherry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar, cherries, baking powder and salt. In separate bowl, mix milk, oil, cherry juice, egg and almond extract.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and pour in liquid.
Stir.
Spoon into tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle on remaining sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen large muffins.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes, molasses, butter, cream, salt, both sugars and canned milk.
Beat eggs until frothy and fold in.
Add spices and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce to 350° and bake until set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into marble size balls. Bake in 400° oven until brown, approximately 10 minutes.

title: sticky wickies
directions: Thaw dough.
Melt oleo.
Combine with sugar and milk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or 2 bread pans.
Sprinkle nuts and cinnamon over this.
Make little balls out of thawed bread dough and set on top of mixture.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: italian green beans
directions: Trim, wash and blanch the green beans in boiling water with salt for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Set aside.
In skillet, heat oil, add garlic and saute until golden color.
Add green beans; heat about 3 minutes.
Season with black pepper.
Serves four.

title: microwave squash casserole(cooking time:  6 to 7 minutes)
directions: Melt margarine in 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Stir in squash, beaten egg, pepper, onion and bread crumbs.
Cook in microwave on Medium to High 6 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Cook approximately one more minute until cheese melts.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook the potatoes and peel.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl until smooth.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook for 7 minutes and drain macaroni.
Mix milk and egg. Cube cheese, cut butter in chunks.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 3 hours.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix ingredients well (not rolls).
Leave dough in squares and press to seal seams.
Cut squares in half and shape into squares. Place a spoonful of chicken mixture on square.
Bring corners together and seal.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix sugars and flour together; stir in water.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick and clear, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Let cook a little (15 to 20 minutes) and pour over hot cake.
Can top with Cool Whip.
Good on raw apple cake.

title: sopa de gandules("pigeon peas soup" with shrimp)
directions: In large stockpot, combine peas, stock, beer, tomato paste, and squash.
Cook until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add shrimp, heating slowly.
Serves 4, as first course.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic in butter for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Add bouillon cube and water.
Cook slowly, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes. Add more seasonings, if desired.
Add shrimp approximately 15 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: the queen's cheese balls
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together, working in flour gradually.
Form into marble sized balls and flatten with fork. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: crab vegetable pastry
directions: *Can substitute 8 ounce carton of soft-style cream cheese with chives and onion.

title: surprise breakfast (made night before)
directions: Mix the eggs, milk and dry ingredients together.
Let set and do following.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with sugar.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix together well the oats, flour, butter, brown sugar and salt.
Topping should be crumbly.
Then add chopped pecans.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna pate
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Place in mold and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: golden sponge loaf
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift together.
Beat egg yolks with rotary eggbeater until thickened slightly.
Add hot water gradually, beating until mixture is very thick and light (about 10 minutes); electric mixer 5 minutes.
Add flavoring to egg yolks, then add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Fold in flour, 1/4 at a time, folding just until blended.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In 2 quart casserole dish place chicken, onion, soy sauce, browning sauce, and reserved pineapple juice.
Stir well and microwave covered 20-25 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Mix together all the remaining ingredients and add to meat mixture. Microwave another 8 minute covered.
Stir in 1 medium green pepper cut up.
Microwave 8 more minutes stirring until thickened and clear.
Fold in 1 medium tomato cut into chunks and let stand covered for 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with rice. This recipe can be made on the stove top but eliminate browning sauce.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add milk and sugar.
Bring to rapid boil.
Boil for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, then Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 pan.

title: junk
directions: Fry hamburger until well done; set aside.
Fry onions and green pepper until tender; add to hamburger.
Boil macaroni until tender. Add macaroni to hamburger and vegetables.
Stir in the can of stewed tomatoes; heat and serve.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with foil.
Spray foil with vegetable cooking spray.
In a large bowl, beat until smooth the corn oil spread, sugar, egg substitute and vanilla.
Add and beat until blended the flour, cocoa powder and baking powder. Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Brownies are done when edges begin to pull away from sides.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Lift foil pan and cut into 28 pieces.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix until it looks like cornmeal.
Spread 3/4 of this on baked pie shell.
Reserve remaining 1/4 for topping.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers.
Chop onions and peppers.
Mix together with salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Bring to boil, remaining ingredients. Add drained cucumbers and bring to simmer.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in lightly greased loaf pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift and mix all spices and flour together.
Then add eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla, potatoes, raisins and pecans.
Mix well. Grease and flour three 1-pound coffee cans.
Pour half full and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together and put into baking pan to form a loaf.

title: robert's chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat cream of chicken soup in skillet.
Leave on low heat and dip corn tortillas in soup, one at a time, in a square pan.
Put a tortilla dipped in soup in pan.
Put chicken, onion and cheese inside and roll it up like an enchilada.
When finished rolling them, top with cheese.
Heat oven to 350° about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry vanilla freeze
directions: Cut each cherry in half.
Read directions on the pudding package.
Follow them to make pudding, using the milk.
Add the cherries and stir.
Divide pudding among 4 dessert dishes.
Freeze for 1 hour.
Easy for kids.

title: nana's banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of oleo (melted).
Spread in cake pan.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients except sugar and nuts in a bowl and set aside.
Mix sugar with oil, mashed banana, strawberries and eggs.
Gradually stir in flour mixture and then nuts.
Pour into well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool in pans for about 10 minutes and then turn out.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine first 4 items, add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well, shape into balls, roll in sugar.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook mushrooms, green pepper and butter until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Stir in cream; cook uncovered until thick and bubbly, stirring.
Gradually stir in 1/2 cup of hot mixture into egg yolk.
Return all mixture to casserole.
Cook uncovered.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Serve over rice.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan until done.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake and pour the can of cream of coconut over the top.
Let cool and spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Top with shredded coconut.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cake freezes well, too.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees in three 9 inch layers.
Cool.
Split layers.

title: apple cake
directions: Place apples, brown sugar and cinnamon into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Add remaining ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: *Good with blueberry or cherry pie filling.

title: wright way potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin until tender.
Test with fork.
Cool, then peel and chop in chunks.
Thin slice celery widthwise.
Thin chop onions and pickles.
Mix all in large container with enough mayonnaise to be very moist.
Salt and pepper to taste; stir well. Slice eggs and stir in.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Slowly add the sugar and beat well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Add the bananas and nuts.
Alternately add the sifted flour ingredients and the milk. Bake in two small or one large loaf pan in moderate oven at 350° for one hour.
Grease tin.

title: turkey ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; form in balls or rolls.
Cover with chopped parsley or pecans.
Freezes well.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add mixture to cornbread in a large pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings which have been mixed together.
Toss together to mix.

title: cheddar cheese drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450.
Cut butter into 1 tablespoon pieces. Set aside.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook together potatoes, carrots, onions and celery until almost tender.
Make hamburger into cakes or balls and fry until just done.
Remove hamburger and brown flour in skillet.
Drain water from vegetables into skillet and cook until thickened.
Put hamburger in baking dish; put vegetables on top and cover with gravy.
Put in microwave on High for 7 minutes or in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain tuna.
Mix celery, onion, pepper and apple in bowl with mayonnaise.
In large bowl, mix macaroni and tuna, then add other mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are blended.
This salad is best if refrigerated overnight.
Garnish with tomatoes and radishes.

title: easy spanish rice
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Or, you may finish cooking in pan on low.

title: okra, sausage, chicken and shrimp casserole
directions: Put shortening in deep skillet or Dutch oven.
When hot, add okra, onions and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Let fry in open skillet on medium heat.
Turn over once or twice.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add chicken, boiled.
Add sausage and dry shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp last.
Cook 20 minutes, covered.
Serve with rice.

title: pork chops and cream of mushroom soup
directions: Use as many pork chops as needed.
Spread small amount of mustard onto each chop.
Bread in flour and fry in Crisco until well done and browned.
Drain and add cream of mushroom soup (measure in soup cans).
Simmer on low heat in pot until soup thickens.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or a little longer, if needed.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in pan; place rolls over that.
Mix dry pudding, cinnamon and brown sugar; sprinkle on top of rolls and dot with stick of butter.
Let rise overnight. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Turn rolls out on serving dish.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the sugar, salt, eggs, cinnamon, oil and grated carrots. combine the flour and soda and add to the first mixture.
Mix well and gently stir in the raisins.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: shrimp-chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl and mix at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Makes 2 cups.

title: homemade granola cereal
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients except broccoli and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly until cheese and margarine are melted.
Add broccoli and salt; cook, stirring frequently until broccoli is heated, approximately 2 minutes.
Turn into casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes until mixture is heated and broccoli is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey cutlets in sweet and sour mint sauce
directions: Dredge turkey in flour.
In a large skillet heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add cutlets and saute 1 1/2 minutes or until juices run clear when pricked with a fork.
Transfer to a plate. Lower heat.
Add sugar to skillet and swirl 1 minute until amber. Stir in vinegar and cook 1 minute until sugar is melted.
Add broth.
Increase heat to high and cook 2 minutes.
Lower heat.
Add mint and turkey.
Cook 1 minute until turkey is heated through. Serves 4.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Beat in 1 egg at a time; add pecans.
Pour in 9-inch shell and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix all together, pour into crust and freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, brown sugar, vanilla and cinnamon. Spread rice into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle raisins over rice.
Pour egg mixture evenly over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot, warm or cold.
Top with yogurt or sour cream if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: smothered dove
directions: Brown doves in heavy skillet in melted butter.
Remove doves to baking dish, breast down.
Add flour to skillet and stir well. Slowly add chicken broth, sherry, salt and pepper; blend well and pour over doves.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chili and corn bread supper
directions: Combine chili, ham, tomatoes, mixed vegetables, onion and chili powder in 3-quart glass casserole; mix well.
Cover. Microwave on High for 15 minutes or until hot, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Put berries and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl and mix before you begin.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix together good.
Roll in pecans (nuts) and parsley flakes. Top with a pimento.
Serve with crackers.

title: riverton squash casserole
directions: Place squash, onion and pepper in a colander over a saucepan containing 1-inch of boiling water and steam vegetables, covered, for 10 minutes or until they are tender.
Transfer with slotted spoon to a bowl and stir in butter, softened crushed crackers, eggs, salt and pepper.
Transfer mixture to a buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Very quick and easy to make.

title: soda bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in an 8 x 4-inch baking pan.
Butter immediately after taking out of oven.

title: easy caramel orange ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Place teaspoonfuls of orange marmalade in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well; set aside.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butters and sugar well.
Add beaten egg.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons full on un-greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle on a little sugar.
Or roll in a mixture of 2 tbsp sugar and 2 tsp cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Place 1 piece of chicken between two pieces of plastic wrap.
Working from the center to edges, pound lightly with flat side of meat mallet to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Remove plastic wrap.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Spray an unheated large skillet with cooking spray.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook for 4-6 minutes or until tender and no longer pink, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
Add mushrooms, onion, water and salt to skillet.
Cook over medium heat about 3 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and most of liquid has evaporated. Add Marsala or sherry.
Heat through.
Spoon vegetables and liquid over chicken.

title: avocado and crab salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatine with water and place over low heat until clear.
Chill to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Mash avocado and blend in other ingredients. Stir in gelatin and chill.

title: quick coconut crust
directions: Melt margarine and add the coconut.
Press evenly into an ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 300°
for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brother bentley's secret sauce for hamburgers
directions: Heat to melt. Spread on hamburgers all during grilling time.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Spread each slice with deviled ham. Roll up tightly.
Brush with melted butter. Chill.
Slice and serve with toothpicks to secure.

title: aloha ham loaf
directions: Blend ham, bread crumbs, egg, milk and ketchup; sprinkle in cloves.
Put sugar and margarine in a loaf pan; heat until melted. Place halved pineapple slices on sugar and margarine in bottom of pan.
Cover with ham mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Invert on platter to serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Beat in remaining ingredients. Chill dough one hour. Roll out on floured surface (we have always used a "Foley Pastry Frame"). Cut out shapes of uniform thinness. Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 5, 7 to 10 minutes depending on thickness and oven.

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Add peaches, sugar, flour and milk, stirring well in same baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mrs. bower's nobby apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add diced apples, nuts and vanilla and then sifted dry ingredients. Grease and flour 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: irene's hobo bread
directions: Sprinkle baking soda over raisins.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand until cool.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into 3 ungreased cans (the kind veggies come in). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If larger cans are used, bake longer.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out half of pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Place crackers in prepared crust.

title: apple fruit salad
directions: Stir dressing ingredients together and cook until thick.
Let cool.
Mix into fruit and refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer celery, onion, mushrooms, zucchini and crackers, spreading soup among layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Finish with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: maraschino cherry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with cherry juice.	Add cut up marshmallows, pineapple and cherries.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: easy stuffed crust pizza
directions: Grease a 9x13 inch pan.
Unroll dough and press in bottom of pan and 1 inch up sides.
Place pieces of string cheese along inside edge of dough.
Fold dough over and around cheese; press dough edges to seal.
Top crust with pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 min. or until crust is golden brown and cheese melts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift baking powder, cinnamon, flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar, oil and egg mixture.
Add carrots and walnuts.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kenney's country store famous chili
directions: In a large pot, saute onion and green peppers in oil.
Add hamburger, cook until not pink.
Add all remaining ingredients. Heat on simmer for 3 hours.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat
egg
yolks until
thick
and
lemon
colored.
Add gradually 1/4 cup sugar and
vanilla.
Beat whites until almost stiff; gradually add 1/2 cup
sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold yolks into whites.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times and add to mixture, folding
in.
Bake in greased waxed paper lined 15 1/2 x 10 1/2
x
1-inch jelly roll pan for about 12 minutes at 375°.
Loosen
sides, turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove
paper,
trim
crusts.
Roll
with sheet of paper inside of
roll.
Wrap
in
towel
until
cool. Unroll, remove paper, spread with
jelly
that is your family's favorite. Roll again, slice and serve for a really good treat.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water.
Mix cream cheese and canned milk together.
Add this to jello mixture.
Place in refrigerator and let cool.
When it begins to thicken, add pineapple, nuts and cherries that have been cut in half.
Place in refrigerator and stir at intervals to keep fruit and nuts from coming to the top.

title: curried chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Brown chicken.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion, green pepper and mushroom to skillet; saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes (with liquid), curry powder, salt, garlic, cloves and Tabasco sauce.
Return chicken pieces to skillet. Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with crusty bread and green salad.

title: country baked tomatoes
directions: Place 8 tomato halves in a baking dish.
Coat top halves with cooking spray.
Bake tomato halves at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and top evenly with the dressing. Broil 3-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until tomatoes begin to brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: apricot fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Blend well.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Boil the broken corn cobs 1 minute and then drain.
Add enough water to make 3 cups.
Add Sure-Jell and bring to a boil. Add sugar and boil 2 to 3 minutes until it jells.
Pour into glasses and cover with paraffin.

title: western corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except 1 cup cheese.
Put in greased 7 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
(Gets better second or third day.)

title: yummy pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Beat in brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Transfer coated pecans to greased pans. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave 30 minutes.

title: texas corn bread
directions: Grease iron skillet.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour in hot skillet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together; drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients and cook 2 hours on high, then turn to low and simmer until you are ready to eat.

title: roast with its own gravy
directions: Brown
the
roast
in
oven
until most all the fat has browned
well
While roast is browning, mix your dry soup mix with the cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour soup over roast
and
cover.
Cook
on
for
3 hours or until tender.
Soup mix makes the gravy.
(When I do this for Sunday dinner, I cook it on 250° during Sunday School and church;
so tender you can cut it with a fork!)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
While still hot, add frosting.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in oblong pan.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into bowl; add chocolate and stir.
Dip spoon back and forth putting into pie shells.
Swirl vanilla and chocolate portions together with knife. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool one hour.
Chill 2 hours.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter until smooth.
Add cubed chicken, salt, pepper, milk and pimiento; mix well.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Place fish in casserole dish.
Mix in bowl the crackers, onion, butter, cheese, garlic salt and salt and pepper; pour over fish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herbed chicken thighs with vegetable-wine sauce
directions: Trim excess fat from chicken; place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with thyme, rosemary, basil and pepper.
Pour wine around chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add rest of ingredients and turn into a well buttered pudding dish.
Dot with butter and pepper.
Bake until firm in slow oven and serve hot.

title: noodle kregel
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain; rinse in cold water and drain again.
Set aside.
heat milk over medium heat in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add cream cheese and 1/2 stick of margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat and allow to cool about 5 minutes.
Then add sugar, oil and citrus peel.
Mix well.
Beat the eggs and stir into the cream sauce.
Place the drained noodles into a large mixing container.

title: peanut butter whimsies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to full boil.
Allow to cook about 1/2 to 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter until melted.
Add oatmeal.
Drop tablespoons of mixture on wax paper until hard.

title: tacos
directions: In skillet, brown beef and green pepper until tender.
Add soups and a small amount of water.
Cook over low heat.
Fill taco shells with meat mixture.
Top with lettuce, chopped tomatoes, chopped onions and Cheddar cheese.

title: rice dessert
directions: Combine the ingredients in the order they are listed.
Chill thoroughly and serve in sherbet glasses.
Garnish with more whipped cream and with a cherry and mint leaf.

title: cheese ball or dip
directions: Grind up beef and onion, then mix in remaining ingredients. Shape into a ball or process it and pour it in a bowl.

title: layered pear and cream cheese salad
directions: Drain pears, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups; bring to a boil.
Dice pears.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Add ginger ale and lemon juice; pour 1 cup into mold. Chill until thickened.
Arrange a few pear dices in mold, pushing them down into design depressions.
(If using a design mold.)
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually blend in remaining gelatin. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining pear dices and the nuts.
Spoon over gelatin in mold.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Will keep indefinitely.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per hot water.

title: ultra rich coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Mix well and add vanilla.
Put in double boiler over medium-high heat. Cook until thick, keeping stirred.
Add coconut.
Pour into pie shells.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar. Beat again.
Brown in oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pork tenderloins with mustard sauce
directions: Pour over meat and put in fridge for 24 hours.
Cover loosely. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover to brown it.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all until well blended. Bake in greased 9 x 12-inch glass pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce 'n spice bread
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: honey fruit salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Set aside. Combine
remaining	 ingredients.
Pour
over
fruit
mixture, stirring gently. Chill.
Yields 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook yellow cake mix as directed and cool.
Crumble a layer of cool cake in a punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed.
Spread over crumbled cake.
Spread can of pineapple with juice over pudding. Add second layer of crumbled cake.
Spread can of pie filling over cake.
Top with container of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Serve and get requests for seconds.

title: whole wheat caramel rolls
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl combine 1/2 cup all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In small saucepan, heat milk, water and shortening until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add warm liquids to flour mixture.
Stir by hand until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in an additional 1/4 to 3/4 cup flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and towel.
Let rise until doubled in size, about 1 1/4 hours.
Yields 16 rolls; serving size, 1 roll.

title: refrigerated slaw
directions: Heat sugar, vinegar, salad oil and spices for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
This will keep 5 or 6 weeks.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Combine crab meat, melted butter and mayonnaise dressing.
Add eggs, well beaten, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste.

title: hot bean and cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine 1 cup tomatoes with next 7 ingredients (1 cup tomatoes through chilies). Spoon tomato mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish coated with the cooking spray. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Top with remaining tomatoes. Yield: 4 1/2 cups.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except black pepper and chopped nuts.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with black pepper and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peach frosty
directions: Combine ice cream, rum, sugar and peaches in container of blender; process until smooth.
Add ice to within 1 inch of container top; blend well.
Yield: 5 cups.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored. Add the granulated sugar and beat until smooth. Stir in the oil and vanilla. Thoroughly stir together flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Add to egg mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and roll to a 1/2-inch thickness. Cut dough with floured doughnut cutter. Fry in deep hot fat (375°) until golden brown, about 3 minutes, turning once. Drain on paper towels. Serve plain or sprinkled with powdered sugar. Makes 24.

title: peppers filled with meat and rice(4 servings)
directions: Drop the peppers into rapidly boiling, salted water and cook them, uncovered, until nearly tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Fill with desired combination of cooked food.

title: marinated crabmeat
directions: Combine all and marinate several hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Add these and sour cream to the butter and sugar mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Chill.
Drop by tablespoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with butter frosting.

title: company stroganoff
directions: In a dutch oven or deep large skillet, heat oil and butter, add mushrooms and onion and saute 2-3 minutes.
Mix flour and dry ingredients; sprinkle over meat and toss to coat meat.
Add meat, chicken broth, beef bouillon cubes, celery seed, parsley (or celery leaves).
Cook until it bubbles good; add evaporated milk, stirring well.
Turn off and cover.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package; drain.
Gently fold sour cream into meat mixture. Serve immediately after adding the sour cream.
Spoon onto egg noodles and serve with salad or vegetable and roll.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Bake in greased spindle cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight in ample water.
Drain the beans and cook in ample water with the baking soda.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Place beans in a 2-quart baking pot with a lid.
Add salt pork and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients with a cup of hot water and pour over the beans.
Add enough additional hot water to cover the beans.
Place the lidded baking pot in a 300° oven for about 4 hours, longer if the beans are not tender.
Stir only once or twice during the cooking process and add more water to keep the beans moist.
Do not drown them.

title: hot dish supreme
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Cook onion and celery.
Add mayonnaise while hot.
In casserole dish, put 3 slices buttered cubed bread; add mushroom mixture.
Add rest of bread layered. Pour egg mixture over; cover and refrigerate 1 hour or overnight. Spread soup over bread and sprinkle with cheese before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (debone chicken) except onion rings.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour onion rings and bake in oven until they are brown (about 5 minutes).
Serve immediately.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Zesty Italian mix until well blended.
Stir peppers, refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Layer and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into four 8-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown meat together and drain excess fat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix ingredients and spoon onto buns.
Top each with Mozzarella cheese, grated.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil and put in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: mint brownie cups
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in medium saucepan.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and mint extract.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Line 12 cupcake liners in muffin pan.
Fill each with two tablespoons of batter.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes until toothpick barely comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar and top with a slice of strawberry.

title: orange-sesame dressing
directions: Good for spinach salad or lettuce salad (romaine, iceberg or green leaf mixture).

title: daddy's quick dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise (whatever amount you want to make) with enough mustard to give it a light yellow color.
Mix in a few drops of lemon juice to taste.
Enjoy with potato chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients to mixture. Add apples, pecans and vanilla. Mix well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Add blueberries, cream cheese, sour cream, pineapple and sugar.
Mix and let jell.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter over medium heat until the meat is brown and the onion is tender.
Season to taste.
Reserve liquid from mushrooms; add 1/2 cup milk or enough to make 1 cup. Stir mushrooms and liquid into meat and simmer for 2 hours.
Place meat in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes over meat.

title: mexican mush
directions: Cook together Ro-Tel tomatoes, taco sauce, pinto beans and ground beef.
(I cook this in my crock-pot all day).

title: quick tea doughnut holes
directions: Heat the shortening (375°).
Beat the oil, egg, milk and vanilla with a spoon.
Mix in the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Drop by a teaspoon into hot shortening.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in sugar, cinnamon-sugar or powdered sugar.

title: chicken cheese rolls
directions: Place split breast between waxed paper.
Pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread each with 3 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Dot with 1/2 teaspoon butter.
Fold ends over filling.
(Some will ooze out during baking.)
Wrap 1 slice bacon around each roll.
Place seam side down in shallow baking pan.
Bake on top rack in 400° oven 40 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear when meat is pierced.
Broil about 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp and golden.
Makes 6 servings.
Per serving, 400 calories.

title: coconut pecan pound cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
water,
butter and coconut flavoring; boil until clear.
Poke holes in cake.
Pour sauce over cake.
Let stand about 4 hours, then take out of pan.

title: vegetable-pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, broccoli or zucchini, tomato and green onion.
Add salad dressing; toss to coat.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients with sour milk being last.
Mix and bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in large kettle until browned.
Add potatoes, cabbage, carrots, celery, tomato juice, rice and bouillon with 1 1/2 cups water to beef mixture; season with basil, thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place in saucepan and bring to boil:
margarine, water, oil and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Beat well; add beaten eggs and beat again.
Add buttermilk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird food
directions: Stir together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.	Fill feeder.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl, add 1 1/2 cups water, sugar, salt and melted shortening.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Add to other mixture.
Mix and add egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat well and add remaining flour.
This can be used before chilling or made ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water in pot.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Mix over low heat until dissolved.
Let cool. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a large bowl and let congeal.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine and sugar together for the bottom of crust; spread evenly in a large pan.
Whip Cool Whip and powdered sugar, then add cream cheese with vanilla.
Spread half of mixture on crust.
Spread pie filling over Cool Whip mixture.
Add remaining Cool Whip over pie filling; chill.

title: chicken, okra and smoked sausage gumbo
directions: Melt butter.
Season chicken with salt and red and black pepper.
Brown in butter and remove.
Brown sausage and remove. Smother sliced okra in oil until brown.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Simmer until wilted.
Add garlic and tomatoes.
Simmer 6 minutes.
Add water and seasoning and bring to boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Add sliced sausage and chicken.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add green onions.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese cookies #2
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Roll mixture into hot dog shaped pieces.
Slice and place on cookie sheet.
Place a walnut piece on each slice.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta frittata
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add garlic and cook 10 seconds.
Add spaghetti, tomatoes, eggs, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Put skillet in 350° oven. Broil for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Mix cooked rice and ground beef.
Place green peppers in casserole dish and fill with rice mixture.
Fill in casserole with the rest of the mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except flour.
Mix well. Gradually add flour.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and cook 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Top with red crystals while hot.

title: easy cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla; mix well.
Spread in pie shell.
Place cherries on top and chill.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into 2 medium or 1 large casserole. Cover. Bake in slow oven (325°) for 3 hours. Stir occasionally. Uncover the last 30 minutes of cooking. Makes about 20 servings.

title: oven roasted red potatoes
directions: Melt butter and garlic in roasting pan/glass ovenware to cover bottom.
Add potatoes.
Cook 1 hour at 375° to 400°.
Turn to brown.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Place sliced apples in pie crust; if apples are tart, sprinkle 1/4 cup extra sugar and then sprinkle the nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and water over apples.
In small mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar; then cut in oleo until it resembles coarse corn meal, then pour over apples.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick pizza crust
directions: Preheat oven to 340 degrees.

title: turkey rice casserole(great for left over turkey after thanksgiving.)
directions: Melt oleo in pot, add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in broth, then milk, add rice, turkey, mushrooms and green pepper.

title: joan's baked beans
directions: Brown onion and hamburger together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangle sheet cake pan.
Melt shortening in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cocoa, sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes.

title: coconut washboard cookie
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly. Add milk, vanilla and coconut, mixing well. Spoon flour into dry measuring cup. Level off and pour measured flour into a square of waxed paper. Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture and stir until smooth. Shape dough into rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Chill overnight or until firm. Slice with sharp knife into 1/4-inch slices. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Press tops with tines of fork. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yield: 6 dozen.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; add baking powder, salt and sift dry ingredients three times.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add 1/3 flour mixture alternately with half the milk, ending with flour.
Beat after each addition until smooth. Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Use icing of your choice.

title: marvell's pound cake
directions: Note: Let everything be at room temperature.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Melt peanut butter and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add ice cream and stir until mixture is well blended.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crushed peanuts or bits of cracker crumbs on top.
Put in freezer.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Lightly grease a large baking pan.
Pour pineapple with juice on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle blueberries over pineapple and pour 3/4 cup of sugar over berries.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over berries and melt butter to drizzle over cake mix.
Pour remaining sugar over butter and sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut through with spoon in several places to allow juice to come through.
Cook 10 to 15 more minutes.
When done, cake mix will be on top and be golden brown.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and put in 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: pizza rolls
directions: In heavy frypan, heat about 1-inch of oil.
Mix all ingredients except wrappers.
Separate wrappers, lay one on flat surface, place teaspoon filling in middle, moisten edges and fold. Press edges to seal.
Slide carefully into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown; remove to paper lined plate.
Repeat until filling is used.
Store remainder of wraps in sealed bag in refrigerator.

title: kitchen bread (germany)
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, brown sugar and butter.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Add egg, sour milk and vanilla to flour mixture.
Sift remaining flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add to butter and milk mixture.
Blend.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Add cinnamon and nuts to reserved mixture.
Sprinkle over batter. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chicken curry casserole
directions: Bake chicken, until fully cooked, and dice.
Mix chicken with all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves approximately 6.

title: red-eye pot roast
directions: Place meat in Dutch oven.
Combine tomato sauce and 1/2 cup wine and add to meat along with orange peel, spices and garlic. Cover and cook at 300° for 3 hours.
Add remaining wine and onions.
Cover and cook for 1 hour longer or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and let stand a few minutes before slicing.
Skim excess fat off juices.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until all is melted and slightly browned.

title: old fashion pot roast
directions: Brown roast in skillet in 2 teaspoons oil. Take out of pan and put in crock-pot. Add the rest of the ingredients. Cook until done or tender, approximately 4 hours on high.

title: pasta salad
directions: *Break pasta in half, cook and drain (4 ounces vermicelli or 1/2 spaghetti and 1/2 shells).

title: homemade onion soup mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Store in an airtight container up to 6 months.
Stir or shake well before each use. Makes 18 tablespoons (about 1 cup).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Suggested fruits:
grapes, melons, pineapple and kiwi.

title: sweet dip
directions: Mix well.
Use apples, bananas or any kind of fruit and dip.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables.
Good on baked potatoes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon gradually.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in oblong cake pan or two loaf pans.
Baking pans should be greased or floured or sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch loaf pan or pour into a couple of empty Pringles potato chips round cans. Cover with foil and freeze until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves a bunch.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl except kisses. Mix on low speed until dough forms. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar and place on cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Top each immediately with a chocolate kiss.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes or until done. Garnish with cooked sliced bacon.
Makes one 9-inch meat pie.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Grate or chop vegetables.
Add salt and mustard seed.
Combine 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water and 2 cups sugar.
Heat to a boil. Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
It will keep in your refrigerator for four months.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour to melted margarine.
Combine eggs with margarine mixture.
Add Karo, coconut and vanilla to egg mixture. Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk; heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; heat until melted, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Combine with sauce in a 2-quart casserole; top with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: lasagna
directions: In hot oil in heavy frypan, brown garlic and onion until soft.
Add beef.
Cook and stir until crumbly.
Mix in salt, pepper and tomato paste blended with hot water.
Simmer sauce uncovered for 30 minutes.
In shallow baking dish, put a thin layer of sauce, half the lasagna noodles, the Ricotta and thin slices of Swiss or Mozzarella.
Repeat with half the remaining sauce, the lasagna, the last of the sauce and Swiss or Mozzarella. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Leave out of oven 15 minutes and cut in squares.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy popcorn balls
directions: Combine butter, vanilla, marshmallows and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Pour over popped corn.
Butter hands and form into balls.

title: pizza bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook sausage with onion and green pepper until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in seasoning, tomato sauce, olives and 2 tablespoons Bisquick.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently for 1 minute.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs together and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until golden, about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: drumstick cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix 2/3 cup crushed peanuts, vanilla wafers and butter together. Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes. Let cool completely.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients and press into pie plate and cook at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: lime jell-o salad i
directions: Pour pineapple and its juice into saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Mix in coconut and buttermilk.
Add pecans, if desired.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bundt pan or ring mold that has been sprayed lightly with cooking spray.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and butter melts.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt to mixture, stirring well.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: s. bean
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan.
Cook until heated through.

title: cranberry nut tea bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add buttermilk, egg and cranberry sauce.
Stir well; do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Can be sliced, toasted and buttered or sliced and served with custard sauce or a "dollop" of whipped cream.

title: steak and ale chicken
directions: Marinate breasts in remaining ingredients for 24 hours.
Cook on ready grill.

title: mini binies
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and lemon juice together.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon together and place in bowl.
Roll out bread slices until thin.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto thinned bread and roll like jelly roll.
Dip bread and mixture into butter, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Freeze on cookie sheet.
Once frozen, place in plastic bag overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Serve warm.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In large roasting pan, combine popped corn and nuts.
Place in oven while preparing glaze.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over warm popcorn and nuts.
Toss to coat well. Bake 60 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool; break apart. Store in tightly covered container.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Make Rice-A-Roni with 1 cup less water than package instructions direct.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Add just enough liquid from artichoke hearts to moisten salad to right consistency.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: aunt dot's passover mandel brot
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift cake meal, salt and starch together.
Fold into egg mixture. Add chocolate chips; mix well.
Form into 2 loaves.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 45 minutes.
Slice while warm.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Warm milk to lukewarm.
Add ammonia.
Stir until dissolved. Mix all ingredients along with enough flour to roll.
Roll very thin and cut.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake on center rack of oven at 350° until golden brown on bottom. Top will not brown.

title: buttercream chunky chocolate frosting
directions: Beat together butter, cream cheese and vanilla until well blended.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in dipping chocolate or chocolate chips.
Microwave for about 2 minutes or until soft and then stir into mixture.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 10 minutes, take out and put grated Cheddar cheese or sliced Cheddar cheese on top.
Finish baking the last 10 minutes with cheese on top.

title: nel's pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients together and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Divide into 4 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn out of cans onto a rack.
Wrap in foil.
Make at least 1 day ahead.
Can also be baked in loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: beef burgundy(serves 6)
directions: Cut beef; tenderize if needed.
Saute garlic and onions until soft.
Remove.
Brown meat in oleo left in pan.
Add beef gravy, salt and pepper.
Return onions and garlic to pan.
Simmer 1 hour. Add herbs and wine.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in half sour cream.
Turn into serving dish.
Dot with remaining cream.
Serve over rice.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix together and bring to boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
To make good chocolate pie, add 1 heaping tablespoonful cocoa per pie.
For coconut pie, put in coconut to taste.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make crust and line a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken in casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add vegetables.
In saucepan, heat broth until just warm.
Add margarine. Add enough water to 1/3 cup flour to make a thin paste to thicken the broth. Add to broth and cook until slightly thick. Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Add top crust which has already been rolled out.
Seal edges.
Cut slits in top of crust for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: wet burrito
directions: Brown hamburger and cumin; add green pepper, onion, chili powder and refried beans.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Heat enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and gravy.
Put meat mixture, lettuce and tomato in soft shell and fold.
Cover generously with heated sauce.
Top with Longhorn or Cheddar shredded cheese.
Microwave "One" for 45 seconds or bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, black olives, avocado or onions on top.

title: homemade chili
directions: Make fire on grill. Put black stuff in it.
Put whole chicken on fire.
Look at it and close the grill.
Go into the house. Real hot - 1° for 5 1/2 hours.
Take it off fire and eat it.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Put in iron frying pan and turn heat on high. Stand and stir with a wooden spoon until water evaporates and goes back to sugar. (Take off stove at first sign of sugar formation but continue to stir until all nuts are covered.)
Pour in shallow pan and put in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: punch slush for a bunch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and freeze.
Set out one hour before using.
Pour 3 quarts ginger ale over slush.
Do not add ice. Punch should have an icy slush floating on top.
Delicious!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a tight container.
Marinate for several hours.

title: overnite coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Cover with tight lid or aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, put on topping of 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 cup nuts (pecans are really good).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting while still warm.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Fry pork chops in Wesson oil; drain.
Place cooked and drained pork chops in pan.
Pour mushroom soup over pork chops.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Serve warm.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips or corn bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread the chicken over the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the drained mushrooms over the chicken.
Cover with the soup which
has been mixed with the half can of milk.
Pour over the chicken.
Cover all with slices of cheese.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush all but 14 wafers to very fine and mix with melted butter.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour softened ice cream into pan (one on top of the other).
Chill.
Spread fudge topping over ice cream.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 4 to 6 hours.
Garnish with remaining wafers and chocolate shavings or Macadamia nuts.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salt water until tender.
Drain. Combine with remaining ingredients, stirring to blend.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt, and cocoa together.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in water or milk to make things wet but do not make too thin. Add small piece of butter.
Pour about 1 cup boiling water into mixture.
Cook until thick then add 1 tsp vanilla.

title: blackberry apple pie
directions: Layer apple slices on bottom crust, then blackberries.
Mix sugar and flour and sprinkle over fruit.
Cover with top crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
May be iced.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: turnip, carrot and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in medium pan; add onions and garlic and saute until tender and golden, about 5 minutes.
Add turnip, potato, carrots and broth.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Strain solids into blender; reserve broth.
Add half and half, ginger, cayenne and cinnamon to vegetables in blender and puree until smooth.
Return puree to broth.
Stir in orange juice and maple syrup and simmer 5 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 2 servings.
Serve with cornmeal-cheese biscuits.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Mix together margarine, powdered sugar, pineapple, chopped nuts, eggs, lemon juice and about 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Arrange ladyfingers flat in dish.
Pour the mixture over the ladyfingers. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.
This is better the second day.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix ingredients together. Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: mechado
directions: Slice beef in serving pieces and brown in cooking oil.
Set aside.
In another pan, saute the garlic, onion and then tomato sauce.
Add meat; cover and cook slowly on low heat, about 20 minutes.
Add the lemon juice, soy sauce, peppercorns, potatoes, bay leaf and salt.
Continue to cook a few more minutes, until the meat is tender.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together peanut butter, sugar and melted butter.
Blend until creamy.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Shape into balls. Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Using toothpick, dip 2/3 of ball into chocolate.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Can be rolled in crushed pecans.
I put in small crock jar.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Lightly toss the first three ingredients together.
Puree a sauce of the last four ingredients in a blender; toss the chicken mixture with the sauce.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed potato chips and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook 2 3/4 cups sugar, Karo syrup, water, salt and vanilla until it is 265° to 270° on a candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar and mix again.
Add the two mixtures together until stiff.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on greased or buttered pan.
Allow to sit 30 minutes.

title: ground beef and vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in a pot and cook for 4 to 6 hours.

title: banana super shake
directions: In blender, combine bananas, lemon juice, water and sweetened milk.
Blend well.
Add ice, blending until smooth.
Serve in frosted glasses.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cornbread should be relatively thin in this size pan and ready to be cut into 1-inch squares.
Mix together all other ingredients and dressing, using most of the jar of Miracle Whip.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease (oleo) 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Stir together in pan all ingredients except chicken breasts.
Lay chicken breasts on top and sprinkle onion mix over top.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add brown sugar; mix well.
Add Bisquick; beat.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix ingredients by hand, pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue.
Brown in 400° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
and
boil
for
minutes
or thick. Take off of heat.	Add
jello and food coloring.
Boil 1 more minute; cool, then	mix
strawberries and pour in baked pie shell. Refrigerate until chilled.

title: blue crab suzy
directions: Saute
in olive oil, onion and green pepper until onion is transparent.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Ragu sauce and 1
cup of water.	Bring to boil, stirring well.
Reduce heat. Add
crab meat
and drained mushrooms.
Mix well.
Bring to a simmer and add dash of garlic salt.

title: asparagus with orange butter sauce
directions: In wide frying pan, bring 1-inch water to a boil over high heat.
Add asparagus; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until barely tender when pierced (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Drain.
Place asparagus on warming serving platter and keep warm.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix cheese, sugar, flour and Ritz crackers (which are crumbled coarsely) and sprinkle over pineapple.
Melt margarine and drizzle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 325°.

title: asian pork chops
directions: In a large shallow baking dish, combine rice wine vinegar, soy sauce, brown bean sauce, scallions, cilantro, chives, garlic and coriander.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole; cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked sausage
directions: Put sausage in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spread onions on top and then apples.
Pack brown sugar over top.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove most of apples and onion.
Drain liquid and serve.
Serves 4.

title: peach or apple dumplings
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick spray; wrap each slice of fruit in crescent roll. Melt butter and stir in the sugar and cinnamon. Pour mixture over dumplings, then pour Mountain Dew over crescent rolls. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Pour Kool-Aid powder in bottom of punch bowl.
Add sugar.
Pour in pineapple juice plus 1 can of water using pineapple juice can. Mix well.
From side of bowl, gradually pour in 7-Up or lemon lime soda.
Using tablespoon, scoop sherbet out and drop on top.
Ice may be added if desired.

title: peanut soup
directions: Combine stock, onion, leek and carrots in a heavy pot.
Bring to a boil; partially cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Blend until smooth.
Bring to a boil, then stir in rice, salt and chili. Reduce heat to low; cover tightly and cook 20 minutes.
Mix peanut butter in 1/2 cup soup until smooth.
Add to the rest of the soup. Cover, then simmer 5 minutes.
Discard chili.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen mocha mousse
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in nuts.
Spread over bottom and sides of well buttered and floured 9-inch pie plate, forming a high edge.
Bake in a 275° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; let meringue cool in oven with door closed for 2 hours.
Mix corn syrup, instant coffee crystals and water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add chocolate; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Blend in milk.
Slowly stir in cream and vanilla.
Cover; chill.
Whip until soft peaks form.
Spoon into meringue crust.
Cover; freeze several hours or overnight.
Top with chocolate curls, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until fluffy at 350°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions; cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Put all ingredients in boiling pot and let come to a boil for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: mrs. parker's peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of margarine in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients, except flavoring, and pour over melted margarine.
Stir vanilla flavoring
into peaches and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crust is brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Slowly add boiling water.
Cook in a double boiler until mixture is thick.
Separate eggs and beat yolks slightly.
Slowly add hot mixture to egg yolks.
Add juice and grated rind and butter. Continue cooking and stirring until mixture is thick.
Cool.
Pour into a cool baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: lania apple cake(great for breakfast)
directions: Mix sugar into Bisquick, then sour cream with the soda already added.
Then mix slightly beaten egg and mix with spoon and spoon into dish.
Arrange apple slices on top and push in the mixture. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top and dot with butter. Bake 35 minutes at 375° in an 8 x 6-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add Jiffy mix to egg mixture, then add onion and green pepper.
Put in well-greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread with sour cream and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash dressing
directions: Grease a large casserole.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fudge cats
directions: Grease 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) pans.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate and shortening.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and eggs; then flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into pans. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 32 (2-inch) squares.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Mix pumpkin, water, oil and eggs. Then bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling over most of the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour pineapple with juice, over the cherry filling.
Using the cake mix dry, spread it evenly over the fruit.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Just before serving, whip 1 cup of whipping cream and fold through entire mixture. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Marinate rabbit in milk for 30 minutes.
Fry slowly in butter until tender and brown.
Season to taste.
Make gravy by adding flour to fat in skillet, blending well.
Then pour in the top milk.
Serve hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line serving dish with vanilla wafers.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Slice amount of bananas as desired into pudding.
Pour pudding over vanilla wafers.
Add miniature marshmallows over top.
Bake at 400° until marshmallows are golden brown, 5 to 10 minutes.
Best served while warm.

title: ham and dijon pastry cups
directions: On lightly-floured surface, roll puff pastry into two 12 x 13-inch rectangles.
Cut each rectangle into twelve 3-inch squares.
Place pastry squares, with pastry corners pointing up, in cups of medium size muffin pan.

title: yummy tropical-delight pizza(in honor of george sholty)
directions: Combine the rice cereal, the butter and the sugar; press into the bottom of a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare creamy filling; spread over crust.
Cover; chill.

title: double apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place sliced apples in large bowl. Sprinkle flour over apples and stir gently until slices are evenly coated.
In small saucepan, combine apple juice concentrate, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir until smooth.
Place over medium heat and stir constantly until thickened.
Pour apple juice mixture over apples, mixing gently until apples are coated.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients together; stir in mayo.

title: scripture cake(king james)
directions: The easiest way to make this big cake is to cream softened butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one by one, then honey and water.
In a separate bowl, place all dry ingredients and stir until thoroughly blended.
Stir in chopped fruit and nuts and finally, the butter/sugar mix.
Beat well and pour into buttered, lightly floured 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Start checking, however, when cake has been baking for an hour.
This cake will serve 30 to 40!

title: lemonade cake
directions: Add water, oil and eggs to regular cake mix and beat 4 minutes. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and poke holes in cake.
Pour glaze (made from 1 can lemonade and 2 cups 4x sugar) over cake while warm. Refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; gradually add sugar, oil, flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add vanilla and apples.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 2 tsp. sugar and cinnamon combined.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna barbecue
directions: Simmer for 15 minutes.
This is a low-fat recipe.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter; add cocoa to taste.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add canned milk to spreading consistency.
Add nuts and vanilla.

title: buttery graham treats
directions: Spray cooking spray on a jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet with sides.
Line pan completely with graham crackers.
In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar and bring to boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Stir.
Sprinkle nuts over graham crackers.
Pour liquid over crackers and nuts. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove while warm!

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Blend with margarine until fine.
Then mix with sugar, salt and raisins.
Blend egg with buttermilk until foamy (about 1 minute).
Gradually, add buttermilk, egg mixture to flour mixture.
Knead bread thoroughly and form into a ball.
Add flour if too moist.
Put about 1 tablespoon flour on bottom of pan. Spread bread into pan (do not let bread touch sides).
Make a cross on top of bread with knife.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bread will turn golden color. Cool, then slice and serve with butter.

title: tandy take cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder, milk, salt, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, wait 1 minute.
Spread with peanut butter.
Put in refrigerator and cool 1 hour.
Melt 8 ounce Hershey bar and spread on top of cake; refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: pizza dip
directions: On ovensafe plate, spread cream cheese, then layer pizza sauce, cheese and toppings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with dip size Fritos, nacho chips or crackers.

title: strawberry pie(sugar-free)
directions: Combine the water and cornstarch; stir completely.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens.
Cool completely.
Add the strawberry Jell-O and Sweet 'N Low; mix completely.
Add cut up strawberries; mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cover; refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip and a few strawberries on top of Cool Whip.

title: chili sauce or salsa
directions: Cook peeled tomatoes, onions and peppers until tender in a heavy skillet.
Then add vinegar, sugar and spices and cook until mixture thickens, stirring often with wooden spoon.
Makes 7 pints.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pudding mix and pineapple (do not drain).
After blended, add Cool Whip, marshmallows and nuts. Stir until well blended.
Chill overnight or at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
with hands.
Make into small balls
