and	let
stand at least 2 hours.
Melt large bag and small bag of chocolate chips in double boiler with 1/2 bar of canning wax.
Dip balls with fork and put on wax paper.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Add Raisin Bran and boiling water.
Bake muffins at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen muffins.

title: coconut orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Store in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: eclairs
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/3 of the graham crackers.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until thick, then blend in Cool Whip. Pour 1/2 of pudding over grahams.
Layer 1/2 of remaining grahams and other 1/2 of pudding mixture and top with rest of graham crackers.
Cook cocoa, sugar and milk in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Then add oleo and vanilla.
Bring back to a boil.
Pour pudding and graham crackers.
Chill before serving.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Cook until done and shred after cooling.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Add brown sugar, margarine and white sugar to oatmeal.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 of the chocolate chips.

title: crumb cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, oil, milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 12 x 18 x 1-inch greased pan (size of pan is important).
While cake is baking, prepare crumb mixture. Melt margarine and butter; cool slightly.

title: reese's
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Melt peanut butter in 2 cup glass measuring cup in pan of boiling water.
Cut cupcake papers to 1-inch.
Place in muffin pans.
To fill, use 1 tablespoons chocolate, 1 tablespoon peanut butter and 1 tablespoon chocolate.
Let each layer firm before proceeding.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake; chill; enjoy it!!
Makes 1 quart.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Set aside the mushroom caps. Chop mushroom stems; combine the rest of the ingredients and saute in butter until soft. Stuff caps and place in baking dish with a little water. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan melt butter; then add soup, water and rice.
Mix together well, then dice up chicken in small pieces and add to pan mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn and rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
In jar, combine next 6 ingredients.
Pour over corn mixture.
Cover and chill several hours.
To serve, stir in tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add 3 cups milk gradually.
Mix until thick and bubbly.
Add one cup of mixture to 4 egg yolks. Mix, then return to mixture and cook a little longer.
Add vanilla and coconut; pour into baked pie shell.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, onion, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce. Mix 2 1/2 minutes. Chill overnight. Shape into ball. Roll in pecans.

title: herbed biscuits
directions: Melt butter and seasoning in a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex pan.
Cut biscuits in 1/4 sections.
Mix all seasoning in butter and roll biscuits in mixture.
Bake in same dish for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put in crock-pot with other ingredients and cook until cheese has melted and dip is very hot. Serve with corn chips.

title: lemon angel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
From 1 lemon with vegetable peeler, cut peel into 1-inch wide strips; wrap in plastic wrap.
Reserve for garnish.
From remaining 2 lemons, grate peel.
Squeeze juice from all 3 lemons.
In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat egg white ingredient packet from cake mix with orange juice and 1 cup water until blended.
With mixer at high speed, continue beating 5 to 10 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally with rubber spatula, until stiff peaks form.
With rubber spatula, fold in cake flour ingredient packet, lemon extract and grated lemon peel just until flour disappears.
Pour batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan with removable bottom.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: cooked finger paints
directions: Mix the flour and salt in an electric skillet.
Add the cold water and stir until smooth.
Add the hot water and stir until boiling.
Boil until clear, then add desired food coloring.
Mix until smooth.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters
and shake in bag.
Place in an 8-inch cake or pie tin.
Boil the oleo and 1 cup sugar and spoon over dough. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.

title: deviled crabmeat
directions: Remove all pieces of shell from crabmeat, taking care to keep crab in as large pieces as possible.
Saute pepper and onion in half of the butter until tender.
Mix remaining butter with flour; stir in milk to make a paste.
Simmer and stir until it thickens. Add pepper, onions, crabmeat, egg, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Grease 6 crab shells and fill with the mixture.
Sprinkle crumbs with paprika over the tops.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: poultry puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until soft.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, chives and pimiento, mixing well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup poultry mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough to top; twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush top with remaining margarine.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet to make crust.
Bake as directed on package.
Let cool.
Mix dressing, mayonnaise and cream cheese; spread on crust.
Top with vegetables and cheese. Cut into small bars.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Gradually add sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk and sour cream. Add vanilla. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nebo slaw
directions: Mix together.
Add 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Mix well and serve.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes with skin on.
Melt butter in large pan.
Slowly add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until thick.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, onions and bacon.
(Reserve 1/4 cup bacon to garnish.) Add cheese and chicken base.
Cook until heated and stir in sour cream.
Top with bacon.
Add extra milk, if needed.

title: dream strawberry salad or dessert
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip and sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in crushed pineapple and pie filling.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Pour into glass bowl and refrigerate before serving.
Top may be decorated with whole strawberries and nut halves.

title: chicken casserole with chinese noodles
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, broth and salt and pepper. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes; pour into casserole.
Top with noodles. Bake, uncovered, about 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased 9-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 or 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpernickler(cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Make into 4 rolls and then flatten out about 3-inches wide.
Brush on cream or egg white, mixed with a little water.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts. Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven until set.
Take out and cut in slices 1/2 or 3/4-inch wide.
Return to oven and bake until crisp in a 300° oven.
Makes lots of cookies and keeps well.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Into a saucepan, pour beet juice. Add remaining ingredients, except eggs.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Boil gently for 10 minutes. Remove cloves and cinnamon.
Put peeled eggs in a quart jar.
Pour the hot spiced mixture over them.
Use a weight or a ball of plastic wrap to keep eggs under the liquid. Cover and keep in refrigerator.
The longer they stay in the refrigerator, the better they are.

title: eggnog salad
directions: Soften Knox in cold water; set aside.
Drain pears, saving the juice.
Add enough water to pear juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in lemon jello and Knox gelatine; cool.
Drain mandarin oranges, saving a few nice sections for garnish.
Blend eggnog and sour cream.
Stir into jello.
Chill until partly set. Fold in fruit.
Put into a 6 cup mold.
Garnish with kiwi fruit and orange sections on top of jello.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl combine all the ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until mixed well.
Add 1 cup raisins and 1 cup chopped nuts. Pour equally between three 8 x 4-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.
Cool before slicing.

title: baked pork chops and beer gravy
directions: Preheat oven.
Rinse chops and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Coat with flour by rolling or shaking in a bag.
Heat oil and garlic in frypan and brown chops on both sides, about 2 minutes per side.
Place chops in a baking dish.
Saute mushrooms and onions in the same pan, about 4 minutes, until slightly tender and top the chops.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add soups, enchilada sauce and chilies. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Lightly grease casserole dish and lay tortillas on bottom.
Top with 1/2 of meat mixture.
Spread another layer of tortillas, then remainder of meat mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and mixture is bubbly.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small nuggets.
Beat buttermilk and egg together.
Add sesame seed to flour.
Batter chicken in buttermilk and egg, then flour and sesame seed.
Fry in electric frypan at about 350° to 375° until golden brown.

title: baked fresh corn
directions: Combine sugar, salt and corn, tossing lightly to mix evenly. Place in lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add milk and stir lightly. Cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Have first 5 ingredients ready in a bowl.
Boil sugar and milk for 2 minutes and pour over the mixture in bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: bacon and cheddar muffins
directions: Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and bacon just until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fold in cheese and bacon.
Divide batter amount muffin cups.
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: yummies
directions: Put oil in pan on low heat.
Add chocolate wafers and melt, stirring often.
Pour over cereal and nuts in large bowl.
Spread mixture evenly.
Cool and break up like peanut brittle.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well; pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 30 minutes at 325°.
When begins to brown, cover with foil to prevent burning.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; spread 1/2 in baking dish.
Save other half for topping.
Put chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise in baking dish; add remainder of stuffing mix on top. Beat together the milk and eggs; pour over top.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Spread soup on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Grate cheese on top the last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add egg.
Make a paste of vinegar, cocoa and food coloring; add to creamed mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper (I omit these ingredients).
Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish.

title: american pierogi
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Layer noodles, potatoes and cheese (mixed).
Top with sauteed onions.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients.
Slice apples, dip and eat!
Tastes like caramel apples.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese for 30 to 45 seconds.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in yogurt and strawberries.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with fruit or plain sugar cookies.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels in milk in saucepan; pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over baked cake.
Add rest of batter; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with milk chocolate frosting.

title: sue's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini. Add dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave baked fish fillet
directions: Arrange fish in dish with thin sections in center.
Arrange onion slices over fish.
Pour margarine evenly over fish.
Arrange lemon slices over onion.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes on High power, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Fish is ready when it starts to flake.
Rest 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in order given. Cook in double boiler until margarine melts and filling is hot. Pour into 2 (9-inch) regular unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil; mix well.
Add cinnamon, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Divide batter into 2 cake pans. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: parsley parm poultry
directions: Tenderize chicken breasts until thin and wide, taking care not to tear or puncture.
When finished, lay out cutlets and place a pat of butter in the center of each one.
Next, put a teaspoon of Parmesan on the butter, then add a piece of parsley.
Wrap chicken from corner to corner as if into a ball.
Flour each piece and cook on a low flame on each side in a pan.
If desired, garnish with Hollandaise sauce and parsley.

title: lemon baked chicken(a tart and delicious way to oven bake chicken.)
directions: Squeeze 1/2 cup juice from the lemons.
Marinate the chicken in lemon juice, refrigerated, at least 1 hour and as long as overnight.
Heat the oven to 350° and butter a roasting pan.
Melt the butter.
Combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge the chicken pieces in the flour mixture and pat off excess.
Put the chicken pieces in the roasting pan.
Drizzle with melted butter and cook in the preheated oven until well browned, 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange glow salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add Jell-O sugar-free instant pudding.
Sprinkle in orange Jell-O; mix and chill.

title: upside-down chocolate cake
directions: Spray bottom of 10 x 13-inch glass pan with nonstick spray. Put coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Mix cake mix by directions on box.
Pour cake mixture over pecans and coconut.
In large bowl, mix confectioners sugar, butter and cream cheese until blended well, then drop mixture throughout cake by large spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Take out 1 hour before baking.
Place chips on top and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: artichoke casserole appetizer
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Place in a casserole and heat for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: myrtle's zyrtles
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan with melted butter.
Layer ingredients in order given.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Disregard instructions on cake mix.
Mix first 3 ingredients. Pour one-half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
It will be puffy and gooey.

title: creole loaf
directions: Slowly fry onions in shortening; add tomatoes when hot.
Stir in corn meal.
Cook and stir 10 minutes.
Remove from fire; stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan and bake in moderate oven at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple-walnut loaf
directions: Prepare cake mix with eggs, oil and water.
Mix well.
Add apples and walnuts with cinnamon.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until pick comes out clean.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: cherry cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Cream ingredients for 5 minutes on high.
Put one vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake paper.
Fill cups 1/2 full with mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with canned cherry pie filling.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars. Add eggs.
Continue beating together. Dissolve baking soda in 1 teaspoon hot water. Add to mixture.
Mix flour and salt.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix well. Stir in vanilla.
Mix well. Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
This is a crisp cookie!

title: refreshing turkey salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, cantaloupe and turkey.
In food processor fitted with metal blade, combine mint, parsley and garlic; process until finely chopped.
Add yogurt; process to blend.
Add yogurt mixture to rice mixture; toss lightly to combine.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions, and add in pudding.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Bring milk and sugar to a quick boil and add marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted. Add coconut; mix well and pour on top of cake in pan.
Frost.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Beat well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mushroom a la graque
directions: Bring all ingredients, including mushrooms to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn into a bowl.
Cool, then marinate overnight in refrigerator. Yields 6 servings.

title: sharon's chantilly cherry cups
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread around sides of dessert shells, roll shells in coconut that was put on waxed paper and place on tray.
Stir almond extract into cherry pie filling and spoon into shells. Chill.

title: chocolate secret cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour; set aside.
Bring to a boil butter, Crisco oil, water and cocoa.
Then pour over sugar and flour.
Mix all other ingredients and combine.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: fritters
directions: Mix well.
With a large spoon, drop batter into greased pan, adding oil as you need it.
Brown both sides until done.

title: play dough(not to be eaten!)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large, heavy skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes stiff and cleans pan like pie dough.
Remove from heat; beat and cool.
Knead like bread until pliable.
Store in airtight bag or container.
If dough gets sticky with time or use, work in flour until stickiness disappears.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place raw rice in bottom of casserole.
Brown pork chops in skillet, then arrange on top of rice.
Place slice of onion, pepper and tomato on top of each pork chop.
Pour beef bouillon over this.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for about 1 hour.
Add water, if necessary.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots; beat with mixer or food processor with other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Be sure cherries are drained.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Chill before serving.

title: buttermilk cookies
directions: Cream the oleo and shortening.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add alternately with the milk.
Drop tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: hot biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in a well-sealed container, in the pantry or refrigerator.

title: fresh peach dessert
directions: Place 1 cup cookies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together sugar and oleo. Carefully drop in small spoonfuls and pat on top of cookie layer. Mix Dream Whip according to package with milk and vanilla. Add powdered sugar.
Carefully fold peaches into Dream Whip.
Sprinkle remaining wafers on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: april point's famous bran muffins
directions: Mix Bran Buds and milk.
Let stand for a few minutes while mixing the other ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix bran mixture with eggs; mix and fold in flour and baking powder.
Don't overmix! Put into muffin liners, 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs and gradually add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Fold in zucchini, raisins and walnuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2-inches).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour and butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 into 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, rhubarb and water.
Spoon onto oat mixture.
Cover with remaining oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Place mixture on top of hamburger buns.
Bake until cheese has melted and lightly browned.

title: peggy hill's corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes in square 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Put flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl and mix well. Add milk and egg.
Stir well.
Then pour the batter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan over melted butter or margarine.
Add the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more to suite the taste.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Place cookies in plastic bag and crush finely with rolling pin. Pour 3/4 of cookies in bottom of rectangular pan.
Mix milk with pudding; set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pudding until well blended.
Pour over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Chill. Best if eaten same day.
(More cookies can be used, if desired.)

title: orange-gum candy cake
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over candy, pecans, dates and coconut; mix well.
Beat eggs; add sugar and cream.
Dissolve soda in milk; add to eggs and sugar.
Add flour. Pour this over fruit mixture; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 250° for 2 hours.

title: mrs. s' russian christmas cookies
directions: Mix sour cream, egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Add whiskey. Gradually add flour; dough must be smooth and elastic.
Roll out thinly.
Cut in strips and twist.
Fry in deep fat.
Drain. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: toad in the hole
directions: On medium heat melt the margarine in the skillet.
Cut a hole in center of the bread.
Lay bread in the skillet and crack the egg so the yolk lands in the hole.
Let cook for 1 or 2 minutes.
Turn and cook 1 1/2 minutes until it is all cooked.
Top with a slice of cheese.
Serve on a plate with salt and pepper.

title: ham and cheese macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; when done put in greased pan.
Then blend in flour and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Melt 6 tablespoons of butter in a pan, then add ham cubes to macaroni mix. Put in milk over macaroni when thick.
Add the cheese and bread; dot with the 2 tablespoons margarine from the 8 tablespoons.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Mix and beat milk and pudding.
Then, beat in ice cream.
Pour over cooled cracker mixture.
Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle on candy bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 1-quart souffle dish.
Place all ingredients in a blender container and blend until smooth. Pour into the prepared dish; dot with a little butter, if desired, and bake 1 hour.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: neiman marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in blender or food processor until it looks like flour.
Cream oleo with white and brown sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Stir in oatmeal, salt, soda, baking powder and flour.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into golf size balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix very well.
Then add remaining ingredients. Makes a very large batch, so will take alot of mixing.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and of desired consistency, as all ovens vary.

title: chocolate cheese bars
directions: Beat cake mix, egg, butter and vanilla together and spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla together and spread over cake. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: black bean salad
directions: Make a potato salad from these ingredients:

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into 9 x 13 greased pan and bake 20 minutes.
While cake bakes, unwrap the caramels.
Melt caramels with 1/2 can Eagle Brand.
Pour over the baked cake and sprinkle with pecans.
Pour rest of batter over this and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Place pineapple and juice in saucepan. Add sugar and butter. Simmer (low) until thin syrup stage. Remove from heat. Add nutmeg, if desired. In buttered baking dish, layer rice and sauce. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned. Excellent with chicken casserole or pork. Serves 8.

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Beat half and half with eggs, add flour and mix.
Split chilies and rinse out seeds.
Mix grated cheese, saving half. Alternate layers of chilies, cheese and egg mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix tomato sauce and taco sauce and pour over.
Add remaining cheese and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl with mixer until smooth. Whip heavy whipping cream in a separate bowl.
Fold whipping cream into cream cheese mixture until mixed through.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and place sliced fresh strawberries (if desired) on the top.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Add next 9 ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil noodles with salt and 1 teaspoon oil.
Drain.
Mix cottage cheese with 2 eggs.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or more.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Layer hamburger, onion soup mix, mushroom soup and Tater Tots in casserole.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 357° for 30 minutes.

title: washday cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
In separate bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour over butter.
Top with fruit.
Sprinkle remaining sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If canned fruit is used I sprinkle only a small amount of sugar over the top.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Spread over bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Top with shredded Swiss cheese (or cheeses). Then spread thawed spinach souffle evenly over cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields one 9-inch quiche, about 4 main course servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and seasonings. Dip breasts in dressing.
Dredge in crumb mixture.
Place in pan. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
I cover after 1/2 hour to keep them moist.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly.
If dough is too stiff, add a little of the liquid identified on the Bisquick box.
Shape into small balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Blend in water and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt and add to mixture. Fold in oats, nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together (except food colorings); knead to mix well.
Divide and color as desired.
Keep in plastic bags or containers with lids.
Refrigerate.
Keeps 6 to 8 months.

title: sweet and sour mushrooms
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; add oil, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and 1/4 cup reserved mushroom liquid. Pour into blender container; blend at medium speed until smooth. Add mushrooms and onion rings.
Cover; refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Before serving, drain off marinade.
Reserve. Serve mushrooms with toothpicks.

title: easter nests
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Fold in noodles and pastel M&M's.
Chill until easy to handle.
On waxed paper, form mixture by 1/3 cupfuls into 3-inch nests.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Place several peanut M&M's in each nest.

title: batter for deep frying fish
directions: To the flour and salt, add ice water, egg and oil.
When ready to deep fry, add the baking powder.
Deep fry in oil at 350° to 375° until light brown.

title: oven chicken cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 8-inch square baking dish (1 1/2-quart) with nonstick cooking spray.
Place chicken breast halves between 2 pieces of plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Working from center, gently pound with rolling pin or flat side of meat mallet until approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each breast with 1/2 teaspoon mustard.
Top each with ham and cheese slices.
Roll up, tucking ends inside.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Cook as directed on package.
Drain.
Spread meat into a baking dish. Spread cheese on top.
Add salsa on top of cheese.
Cut a few scallions and place on top of the salsa.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, one at a time; beat. Add banana puree, mix well. Add dry ingredients with nuts. Put in paper lined muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix well with hands until crumbly.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir 2 or 3 times during the 12 minutes.
Cool.
Put half in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Reserve the rest.

title: hand and body cream
directions: Unibase can be purchased at most drugstores.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients well.
Spoon into lightly greased ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle top with toasted almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip devil's food cake
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in bowl and put into pan.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip topping and cherry.
Very rich.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: popcorn snack mix
directions: In a large greased roasting pan, combine popcorn, cereal and peanuts.
In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat.
Quickly stir in vanilla and baking soda until mixture is light and foamy.
Immediately pour over popcorn mix.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Yield: about 5 1/2 quarts.

title: yogurt fruit pops
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in a small bowl; chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Beat until well blended. Divide among 8 (3 ounce) paper cups.
Place wooden stick in each. Freeze several hours.
(If keeping longer than overnight, wrap individually in plastic wrap.) To serve, peel cup off "pop". Serves 8.

title: brownies(betty crocker)
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening over hot water.
Mix rest of ingredients into mixture.
Bake in saucepan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect doughnuts
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs with sugar and butter until very light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Scrape sides of bowl occasionally.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
At low speed, gradually beat buttermilk into egg and sugar mixture.
Add flour mixture gradually; beat at low speed just until smooth.
Dough will be soft.
Then deep fry.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Place eggplant slices on baking sheet.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes on each side until brown.
Heat oven to 400°.
On the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish, spread some sauce to cover bottom of dish. Place a layer of eggplant on top.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of each cheese and repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheeses and sauce.
Cover dish with foil and bake for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: insanity wings(warning:  don't serve to children and wimps.)
directions: Mix egg and milk together and coat chicken with mixture. Place flour in bag with 2 to 3 pieces of chicken at a time and shake well.
Place chicken into hot oil and cook until done (golden brown in color).
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and place cooked chicken into mixture and coat thoroughly.
Remove from bowl.

title: chinese meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Mix all ingredients except bacon. Place in baking dish. Cool and freeze. Thaw slightly. Top with the 3 slices of bacon. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cookie cake
directions: In large saucepan, bring 1 stick margarine, Crisco, 3 tablespoons cocoa and water to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and sugar and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, salt, vanilla and soda; mix well.
Pour into jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Bring to a boil chocolate and water.
Let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and sour milk.
Stir well.
Then add the cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven. Can frost with chocolate or vanilla frosting.

title: caramelized sauerkraut
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° to 350°.
Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Add rest of ingredients and mound up on lettuce leaves.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits reserving 2 Tbsp. of each juice. Arrange fruit in baking dish. Combine juices, melted margarine, brown sugar, and curry powder.
Mix well and drizzle over fruit.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Good served with ham, turkey, or lamb. Serves 8 to 10.

title: white christmas cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring margarine or butter and 3/4 cup water to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add baking bar; stir until melted.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and rum extract; set aside.
Stir together 1/2 cup of the flour and the pecans; set aside.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix flour,
salt,
sugar
and spices.
Add oil and beat well. Then add eggs and buttermilk.
Gradually add figs, nuts and the soda
mixture.
Pour into a greased flat pan and bake at 325°
for 45 minutes.
While cake is still hot, pour glaze over it.

title: soft spicy hermits
directions: Mix wet ingredients well, then add sifted dry ingredients. Mix well.
Press onto large cookie sheet (one with sides), greased or sprayed with cooking spray.
You have to use your hands to spread batter.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: allie's fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple; save.
Mix juice, sugar, cornstarch and egg.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Set aside to cool.
When mixture is cool, stir in pineapple chunks, cheese and pecans.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: honey pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare crust.
With electric mixer, beat eggs until foamy, about 1 minute.
Add honey, milk, pumpkin, spice, salt and orange juice concentrate.
Beat until well blended.
Pour pumpkin filling into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Garnish with orange zest, if desired.

title: carrot-coconut salad
directions: Measure all ingredients, except lettuce, into a mixing bowl. Use forks to toss together lightly until dressing is well distributed.
Arrange lettuce cups on salad plates and lift salad lightly into cups.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana whole wheat bread(diabetic)
directions: With electric mixer, beat margarine, sugar replacement, eggs and banana until smooth.
Sift together twice the all-purpose flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir whole wheat flour into the all-purpose flour mixture.
Add dry ingredients with boiling water to the banana mixture (add extra water if mixture is too dry). Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool slightly in pan.
Remove to wire rack for final cooling.
Cool slightly in pan. Remove to wire rack for final cooling.
Yields 1 loaf or 16 slices. Exchange, 1 slice:
1 bread, 1 fat.
Calories, 1 slice:

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla extract. Sift in dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal, cornflakes, pecans, raisins, coconut and candied cherries.
Work with hands until well mixed. Form into small balls and press slightly on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 medium-sized cookies.

title: roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Wipe loin pork with damp cloth.
In mixing bowl, combine salt, pepper, thyme and nutmeg.
Mix well. With fingers, rub the mixture over surface of pork, mainly on fatty part.
Place roast, fat side up, in roasting pan. Scrape carrots. Slice carrots and scatter around roast.
Peel onion and slice into rings. Scatter around roast.
Add cloves. Cut celery and add to roast. Add 1/2 cup beef stock, parsley
and bay leaf. Pour 1/2 cup wine or water around roast.
Add 1/2 cup beef stock.

title: jello fingers
directions: Mix Jell-O, gelatine and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares or any shapes desired.

title: coconut cream pie(8-inch pie)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Add milk and egg yolks. Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens, about 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour into pie shell.

title: strawberry-banana shakes
directions: Peel and cut bananas into six or eight pieces and freeze.
Put fruit and juices in blender or food processor and puree.
Add yogurt and blend about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.
